4c0a5745-0b2a-4810-a2a1-1b2fd1b5a54e	\N	en	Stop the Genocide! Human Chain Protest	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.159851	2026-01-05 11:55:51.159851	stop-the-genocide-human-chain-protest	published	Friday, August 30th at 6:00 PM📍 Aleksanterinkatu, Three Smiths Statue, Helsinki\n\nThe genocide of Palestinians in Gaza has been ongoing for nearly 10 months. On average, Israel kills 130 Palestinians every day.\n\nWe demand that:\n❗️ Finland immediately calls for a permanent ceasefire in Gaza\n❗️ The genocide of Palestinians ends, and Finland supports South Africa's genocide charge at the ICJ\n❗️ The end of arms trade between Finland and Israel\n\n🪧 Please bring only Palestinian and/or Finnish organizational flags. We do not permit racist (including anti-Semitic or Islamophobic), sexist, or otherwise discriminatory texts and symbols.\n\nOrganizers: Sumud, Palcif, ICAHD Finland, AKYS, Finnish Peace Committee	Aleksanterinkatu	admin_mohammad	admin_mohammad	2024-08-28 03:00:00	\N	\N	2024-08-28 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Untitled-1.jpg	["A maroon poster with white text reads, \\"STOP THE GENOCIDE, human chain.\\" Below, there are red poppy illustrations. It continues, \\"30.08.2024 at 6pm, Helsinki, Aleksanterinkatu, Three Smiths Statue.\\" The border features wave-like patterns."]	[]	["Aleksanterinkatu"]	["SUMUD"]
59584690-d73c-438c-b02e-18896e5d4bf1	\N	en	Justice for Gaza	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.160482	2026-01-05 11:55:51.160482	justice-for-gaza	published	⚖️ Justice for Gaza – Demonstration on 3.11.2024 at Helsinki, Railway Square, 2:30 PM\n\nFor over a year, we have witnessed genocide live, with clear evidence brought to us by local journalists. On November 2nd, we recognize the International Day to End Impunity for Crimes Against Journalists. In this time, Israel has killed 168 Palestinian journalists and media workers, injuring 360 and detaining 60. Attacks on journalists are war crimes.\n\nThis is only one part of the atrocities Israel has committed through its settler-colonial project. Brutal bombardments from air, land, and sea continue, causing civilian casualties, displacement, and destruction. A new UN Commission report confirms what we have seen: Israel is committing bloody war crimes and crimes against humanity, rooted in its unlawful occupation and refusal to comply with International Court of Justice orders.\nThe silence of the international community is more than shameful—it’s a blatant display of complicity. Join us to demand justice for Gaza. Join us to demand action!\n\nWe demand:\n❗️An immediate ceasefire\n❗️An end to the genocide in Gaza\n❗️A halt to all arms trade with Israel and a ban on products from illegal Israeli settlements\n\n🪧 Please bring only the flags of Palestine and Lebanon. Racist (including anti-Jewish or Islamophobic), sexist, or otherwise discriminatory texts and symbols are not allowed.\n\nOrganizers: Sumud - the Finnish Palestine Network, Palestinian Community in Finland, Finnish Peace Committee, ICAHD Finland, Finnish-Arab Friendship Society.\nIllustration: Hebron tatreez motif “scale,” digitized by TiraZain https://www.instagram.com/tirazain.initiative/	Helsinki Railway Square	dahn_admin	dahn_admin	2024-10-30 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-10-30 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/event.jpg	["Black background with text announcing a demonstration for \\"Justice for Gaza!\\" on 03.11.2024 at 2:30 PM in Helsinki, Railway Square. The design features a symmetrical, colorful pixel art pattern in the center."]	["Demonstrations"]	["Helsinki Railway Square"]	["PALCIF|SUMUD"]
2c3e7c1d-ac86-423c-a0be-1dec8574a6d0	\N	en	Gaza Fights For Freedom – film screening	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.165286	2026-01-05 11:55:51.165286	gaza-fights-for-freedom-film-screening	published	The UN's day of solidarity with the Palestinian people is on the 29th of November. In light of this, we are hosting a film screening on the 30th of November from 1 PM to 2.30 PM. The screening will be held in the Aine Art Museum's downstairs auditorium.\n\nThe document Gaza Fights for Freedom (dir. Abby Martin) brings to light an important part of Palestine's modern history, the Gaza Great March of Return demonstrations through the years 2018-2019. The demand was for an end of the Israeli blockade and the right of return for refugees.\n\nAfter the screening we can discuss the document and the thoughts spurred by it. The Aine Art Museum closes at 3 PM on Saturdays, so we can move from there to a cafe, for example.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-22 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-22 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/5-1.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
accf4381-3682-4853-b019-79624c32f466	\N	en	19 March 2024 – TAMPERE	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.150992	2026-01-05 11:55:51.150992	19-march-2024-tampere	published	Join us for an impactful evening as we come together to watch “Foragers” (Palestine 2022) and discuss the urgent theme of environmental justice 🎥🌱\n\n⏰ 19.3.2024, 17-19:30\n📍Tampere University, Linna K103\n\nForagers depicts the dramas around the practice of foraging for wild edible plants in Palestine. The film employs fiction, documentary and archival footage to portray the impact of Israeli nature protection laws on these customs. Movie in Arabic with English Subtitles.\n\nThe movie is followed by a discussion about environmental justice in English. Panelists will be announced later.\n\nThe event is part of Israeli Apartheid Week, during of which we aim to raise awareness about Israel’s occupation, settler-colonialism and apartheid, while building support for the Palestinian-led BDS movement.	Tampere University	admin_stanislav	admin_stanislav	2024-03-19 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-03-19 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/WhatsApp-Image-2024-03-15-at-09.15.35.jpeg	["Poster for an event titled \\"SUMUD TAMPERE: Foragers (Palestine, 2022)\\" featuring a movie screening and discussion on environmental justice. Date: 19.3.2024, Time: 17:00-19:30, Location: Tampere University, Linna, K103. Background shows a woman and abstract art."]	["Movie"]	["Tampere University", "Linna K103"]	[]
9e64e837-ffcb-4ca2-b281-f9f76f2a7658	\N	en	the sign-making workshop for families on Friday	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.152806	2026-01-05 11:55:51.152806	the-sign-making-workshop-for-families-on-friday	published	Welcome to the sign-making workshop for families on Friday, May 3rd at 15-19 in Tekstin Talo! Let's make signs for Sunday's demonstration! 🪧🇵🇸\n\nMaterials for the signs are available on site in limited quantities. We recommend bringing your own cardboard and stick for the sign making. 🎨🖌🖍\n\nFamily march for Palestine will be held on Sunday May 5th at 15-17! 🇵🇸🕊🍉\n\nThe demonstration will begin with a march at the pace of children from Rautatientori to Kansalaistori.\n\nThere will be various activity points at Kansalaistori for children, including colouring activities, jewelery making and face glitter.\n\nThe sign-making workshop and demonstration is organised by a group of education professionals.\n\nWelcome! ❤️‍🔥	\N	admin_mohammad	admin_mohammad	2024-05-06 03:00:00	\N	\N	2024-05-06 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Snapinsta.app_440965736_17869549374096082_3485734218746945582_n_1080.jpg	["A colorful poster for \\"kylttipaja\\" event on may 3, 2024, featuring diverse cartoon characters including one in a wheelchair, interacting and holding signs, framed by a decorative border. text details event time and location."]	[]	[]	[]
23ac1c6e-9947-4174-abb7-bc44011926e4	\N	en	Oulu: Justice for Palestine demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.18293	2026-01-05 11:55:51.18293	oulu-justice-for-palestine-demonstration	published	The ceasefire brings some relief in Gaza, but the apartheid and genocide are far from over. Now Israel is focusing its efforts on West Bank where at least 10 people have already been murdered since the start of the ceasefire. Come show your opinion because the work is not over yet. The government of Finland needs to respect international law by ending arms sales with Israel and by defending the right to self-determination of Palestinians.\n\n📍: Kauppurin keidas\n⏰: Saturday 25.1 at 16.30	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-01-24 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-01-24 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/5-1.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
2cc26a12-5f66-45b9-9305-a8bedf5134ea	\N	en	Keskustelutilaisuus: Kansainvälinen solidaarisuus globaalin etelän ja pohjoisen välillä	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.154583	2026-01-05 11:55:51.154583	keskustelutilaisuus-kansainvalinen-solidaarisuus-globaalin-etelan-ja-pohjoisen-valilla	published	Keskustelutilaisuus: Kansainvälinen solidaarisuus globaalin etelän ja pohjoisen välillä\n\n🕒 Tiistaina 11. kesäkuuta klo 17.15\n📍Telakka-ravintola, Tampere\n\nKäynnissä olevan Gazan kansanmurhan vuoksi Palestiina on noussut dekoloniaalisen aktivismin ja globaalin solidaarisuuden yhdistäväksi voimaksi.\n\nSolidaarisuus tarkoittaa toimintaa, mutta pyrkimykset yhdistää globaali etelä ja pohjoinen kohtaavat usein ongelmia, kuten valkoisen pelastajan syndrooman ja representaation puutteen. Miten voimme siirtyä sortavista valtarakenteista merkityksellisiin liittoumiin ja transformatiiviseen toimintaan? Mitä dekolonisoiva solidaarisuus tarkoittaa käytännössä?\n\nLiity keskusteluumme kuulemaan intersektionaalista ja dekoloniaalista näkökulmaa aiheeseen. Panelisteina Javiera Marchant Aedo, Noora Dadu ja Helga West, jotka ovat aktiivisesti mukana taistelemassa erilaisia kolonisaation ja sorron muotoja vastaan. Keskustelua moderoi Lili De Paola. Tapahtuma on englanniksi.\n\nTapahtumassa on myös mahdollisuus tutustua ja ostaa Sumudin upeita tuotteita, joiden tuotto menee aktivismimme tukemiseen.\n\nTapahtuma on osa Suomen Lähi-idän ja Pohjois-Afrikan tutkimuksen kollokviota "Decolonizing Middle Eastern Studies – Critical Perspectives and Emerging Debates", jonka järjestävät Suomen Lähi-idän instituutti ja Tampereen yliopisto.	\N	admin_mohammad	admin_mohammad	2024-06-07 03:00:00	\N	\N	2024-06-07 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Untitled.jpeg	["Event poster titled “International Solidarity Between the Global South and the Global North” with details. Featuring speakers: Javiera Marchant Aedo, Noora Dadu, and Helga West, at Telakka restaurant, Tampere on Tuesday, June 11, 2024, 5:15 pm. Organized by SUMUD."]	[]	[]	[]
2718b497-b84c-4bed-b77e-11c90f412544	\N	en	Workshop: Poems for Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.156147	2026-01-05 11:55:51.156147	workshop-poems-for-palestine	published	Join us in writing poems for Palestine! In this workshop, you will hear an introduction to the significance of poetry in Palestinian culture and get the chance to try your hand at collage and blackout poetry. The theme of the poems will, of course, be Palestine, and as you create, you'll have the opportunity to reflect on the topic with like-minded people and learn ways to get involved in activism. At the end, participants can present their works and, if they wish, donate their poems to Sumud Tampere’s zine project.\n\nThe workshop is free and open to everyone, from beginners to experienced poets. The first 15 participants will be admitted! We will provide the supplies and materials; just bring your creativity and solidarity. The workshop will be conducted in both Finnish and English.\n\nThe workshop is organized by Sumud Tampere as part of the Musta Pispala festival.	\N	admin_mohammad	admin_mohammad	2024-07-04 03:00:00	\N	\N	2024-07-04 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/event1.jpg	["A poster with a retro design features the text \\"Poems for Palestine\\" in colorful, mismatched letters. Below, it states the event details: \\"Pispalan kirjasto, 13.07, 16-17:30, Sumud Tampere\\" against a dark brown background with wavy lines on top."]	["Workshops"]	[]	["SUMUD"]
b9096a25-12d2-4c1e-94ff-3070e8911c8d	\N	en	Human Chain Demonstration - Stop the Genocide!	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.157415	2026-01-05 11:55:51.157415	human-chain-demonstration-stop-the-genocide	published	Human Chain Demonstration - Stop the Genocide!\n\nOn Saturday 6th of July at 4 PM\n📍Kaivokatu, Helsinki\n\nThe genocide of Palestinians in Gaza is soon reaching 9 months. We demand:\n❗️Finland to demand a permanent ceasefire in Gaza\n❗️End the genocide of Palestinians and support South Africa’s genocide charge in the ICJ\n❗️Finland to end arms deals with Israel\n\n🪧 Please bring only the flag of Palestine and/or a Finnish organization. We do not allow racist (including anti-Jewish or Islamophobic), sexist, or otherwise discriminatory texts and symbols.	Kaivokatu	admin_mohammad	admin_mohammad	2024-07-04 03:00:00	\N	\N	2024-07-04 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/WhatsApp-Image-2024-07-04-at-17.38.22.jpeg	["Poster for a demonstration with the text \\"HUMAN CHAIN, Stop the genocide!\\" in bold red and black, scheduled for Saturday, 6th of July 2024 at 4 pm at Kaivokatu, Helsinki. It lists the organizers at the bottom and features an illustration of people forming a human chain.", "A poster for a peaceful protest in Helsinki on July 6, 2024, at 4 PM, with people standing in a chain from behind. The text reads \\"IHMISKETJU\\" (Human Chain) and \\"Loppu kansanmurhalle!\\" (End the genocide!). Organized by various Palestinian support organizations."]	["Demonstrations"]	["Kaivokatu", "Helsinki"]	["Organizer Name|SUMUD"]
712b4ff4-fceb-482c-a0aa-fa1b709202c8	\N	en	Sound of Starvation - March Against the Genocide	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.158366	2026-01-05 11:55:51.158366	sound-of-starvation-march-against-the-genocide	published	A high risk of famine persists in the Gaza Strip as long as hostilities continue and humanitarian access remains restricted. 96 % of the population in Gaza are likely to face crisis or worse levels of acute food insecurity between 16 June and 30 September, and 22 %, half a million Palestinians in Gaza are projected to face catastrophic levels of acute food insecurity.\n\nMore than half of the population does not have any food to eat in the house, and over 20 % go entire days and nights without eating. We demand:\n\n❗️Finland to demand a permanent ceasefire in Gaza\n❗️End the genocide of Palestinians and support South Africa’s genocide charge in the ICJ\n❗️Finland to end arms deals with Israel	Rautatientori	admin_mohammad	admin_mohammad	2024-07-09 03:00:00	\N	\N	2024-07-09 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Untitleden.jpg	["A graphic with a red background shows kitchen utensils and the words \\"Pots & Pans.\\" Text reads: \\"Sound of Starvation - March Against the Genocide! Friday 12th of July 6 pm Railway square, Helsinki.\\" Organizers listed include multiple Palestinian support organizations.", "A red and white poster promotes a protest march. Illustrated pots and pans form the phrase \\"Pots & Pans.\\" Below, text in Finnish reads: \\"Nälähädän ääni. Marssi kansanmurhaa vastaan! Perjantaina 12.7 klo 18 Rautatientori, Helsinki.\\" Organizers' names are listed at the bottom."]	[]	["Rautatientori", "Helsinki"]	["PALCIF|SUMUD"]
a661cd30-d1f9-4dc2-8d10-5d7e18861118	\N	en	Sumud’s Palestine Summer School	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.159273	2026-01-05 11:55:51.159273	sumuds-palestine-summer-school	published	\N	\N	admin_mohammad	admin_mohammad	2024-08-05 03:00:00	\N	\N	2024-08-05 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Untitled.jpg	["A promotional poster for the 1st Palestine Summer School. The design features a red and white motif with poppies and the map of historic Palestine. Text in Finnish, Arabic, and English gives details about the event dates (23-25.8.2024) and location (Pirkanmaa)."]	[]	[]	[]
d25fa937-c15e-4d57-90a6-dbf453f8ce67	\N	en	Tampere: Boycott Eurovision demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.183372	2026-01-05 11:55:51.183372	tampere-boycott-eurovision-demonstration	published	The 8.2. Eurovision demonstration will take place at 17:00 starting from Keskustori. There we will hold speeches and sell Palestine themed products to help Gaza. After that we'll be marching on the streets.\n\nPlease keep in mind that only the Palestinian flag should be raised at our demos.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-01-27 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-01-27 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/1-4.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
0d5204fa-0416-4ab3-bd5a-b8819ace3480	\N	en	Helsinki: The Silencing of Palestine Solidarity in Germany	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.183791	2026-01-05 11:55:51.183791	helsinki-the-silencing-of-palestine-solidarity-in-germany	published	Time: 27.2.2025 at 11:15 – 13\nVenue: Lecture hall Suomen laki, 1st floor, Porthania, Yliopistonkatu 3, University of Helsinki\n\nPlease register for the seminar latest 25.2. at https://elomake.helsinki.fi/lomakkeet/133540/lomake.html\n\nPalestine solidarity movements have faced criticism and suppression across Europe and the United States. In Germany, the policing and suppression of pro-Palestinian activism have been particularly harsh. Those who advocate for Palestinian rights, call for an end to the genocide in Gaza, and criticize the Israeli occupation have experienced legal reprisals and public hostility. The media and authorities have frequently labelled pro-Palestine demonstrations and organizations as anti-Semitic, and individuals participating in them as Israel-haters, which has led to the marginalization and silencing of voices critical of Israeli policies. Scholars argue that the emphasis on Israel’s security as Germany’s Staatsräson (reason of state) has placed the moral alignment of Germany’s citizens with immigrant backgrounds under heightened scrutiny. While the policing of the Palestine solidarity movement is not new, an increasing number of cancellations of international artists, scholars, and other individuals whose opinions deviate from this state policy have taken place during the last sixteen months. In the current atmosphere, individuals and groups are reluctant to speak out or show solidarity with Palestine for fear of facing legal consequences, public backlash, or being branded as extremists.\nThis seminar will explore the particularities of the German case. Through two lectures and discussion, we will examine the challenges created by various resolutions and legal actions that constrain the expression of criticism of Israel and solidarity with Palestine. The seminar will shed light on the struggles faced by those advocating for Palestine solidarity at university campuses in Germany.\n\nThe speakers:\nProf. Dr. Schirin Amir- Moazami, Free University of Berlin\nDr. Nahed Samour, Radbound University\nThe event will be moderated by Dr. Liina Mustonen (University of Helsinki).\n\nBios of the speakers:\nSchirin Amir-Moazami works as a professor of Islam in Europe at the Institute of Islamic studies at Freie Universität Berlin. She studied Political Sciences and Sociology in Frankfurt/Main, Berlin, Aix-Marseille, and Paris, and holds a PhD from the European University Institute in Florence (Department of Social and Political Sciences). Her research interests encompass critical secular studies, political theory, post- and decolonial studies, and politics of the body. She has published widely on topics related to Muslims in Europe, especially in Germany and France with a focus on political secularism, politics of knowledge production, body politics and governmentality. Her recent monograph Interrogating Muslims. The Liberal-Secular Matrix of Integration was published in 2022. Currently, she is working on a research project which analyses bureaucratized knowledge and the logics of preventing “Islamic extremism” in Germany.\n\nNahed Samour, Research Associate at Radboud University, has studied law and Islamic studies at the universities of Bonn, Birzeit/Ramallah, London (SOAS), Berlin (HU), Harvard and Damascus. She was a doctoral fellow at the Max Planck Institute for European Legal History in Frankfurt/Main. She clerked at the Court of Appeals in Berlin and held a Post Doc position at the Eric Castrén Institute of International Law and Human Rights, Helsinki University, Finland, and was Early Career Fellow at the Lichtenberg-Kolleg, Göttingen Institute for Advance Study. She has taught as Junior Faculty at Harvard Law School Institute for Global Law and Policy from 2014-2018. From 2019-2022, she was Core Emerging Investigator at the Integrative Research Institute Law & Society.\n\nThe seminar is organized by the project The Middle East in Berlin (Kone foundation, 2024-2027) and The Centre for Research on Ethnic Relations and Nationalism (CEREN), Swedish School of Social Science, University of Helsinki\n\nhttps://www.helsinki.fi/…/ethnic-relations-and-nationalism\nhttps://www.facebook.com/ceren.helsinki/\nhttps://www.instagram.com/ceren_helsinki/	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-01-31 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-01-31 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Screen-Shot-2025-01-31-at-13.35.13.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
f6dfb685-517e-405d-80b0-5031abc48186	b981826c-2c80-456d-af7e-d64a26916d40	en	Cafe Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.161174	2026-01-05 11:55:51.161174	cafe-palestine	published	Cafe Palestine x onboarding session on Friday 1st November @ Venetsia-talo, Lapinlahden Lähde🇵🇸\n\nWelcome to the very first Cafe Palestine organized by Sumud Helsinki chapter! The first cafe will be a cozy Friday evening gathering to spend some time with beautiful people in Palestine solidarity movement, get to know each other & talk about Palestine. We will serve coffee, tea and some snacks! Feel free to bring something to share.\n\nOur first Palestine Cafe will include an onboarding session 18-19, as we are looking for new volunteers in Sumud Helsinki chapter! 📢 Come early to hear more about our work in Helsinki and find a suitable way for you to participate. 🕊️🇵🇸\n\nRegistration link here and in our bio: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfZxGgnoeu5-Pq4X6pOhb4oF33ERPm5iATbBj3GqPWBFcPU3g/viewform\n\nAccessibility info:\nThe space is on the ground floor of the building. There are two steps at the door outside, but with a ramp it is possible to get in with a wheelchair. The toilet inside is small.	Venetsia-talo	dahn_admin	dahn_admin	2024-10-30 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-10-30 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/cafepalestine.jpg	["A promotional poster for \\"Cafe Palestine\\" event on Friday, November 11, from 18:00 to 21:00 at Avoin tila, Lapinlahden Lähde. Features a cup of coffee with a Palestinian flag and diverse cartoon people at the bottom.", "Cafe Palestine event poster with a steaming cup of coffee featuring the Palestinian flag. Details: Friday, 1.11, 18-21 at Avoin tila, 1krs, Venetsia-talo, Lapinlahden Lähde. Includes diverse cartoon characters and an invitation for a cozy evening gathering."]	["Cultural events"]	["Venetsia-talo"]	["SUMUD Helsinki"]
9b6c38d0-7d74-4420-8efb-90ffa1d3879a	\N	en	DISCUSSION: Palestine beyond genocide - looking to the future	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.162237	2026-01-05 11:55:51.162237	discussion-palestine-beyond-genocide-looking-to-the-future	published	Saturday 16.11.24 at 4:15 pm\nLanguage: Finnish\nLocation: Korjaamo, Töölönkatu 51, Helsinki\n\nIn the ongoing genocide Israel is trying to wipe out Palestinians. For over a year, attention has focused on the progression of the genocide, on the support for it, or attemps to stop it. But what will happen once the genocide is over? How has the genocide changed the view of where Palestine is going - among Palestinians, in Finland, in Europe? Earlier there was talk of the two-state solution or one democratic state - how do they look now?\n\nOur panelists are journalist and author Umayya Abu-Hanna, activist Noor Assad, politician who has worked as a MEP and minister in the Finnish government Sirpa Pietikäinen (kok), and social antropologist Tiina Järvi.\n\nThe event is chaired by Syksy Räsänen, vice-chair of Sumud - the Finnish Palestine Network. The event s part of the Refugee Film Festival program.\n\nFree entry!	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-06 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-06 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/refugee-film-festival-discussion-2.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
6f3a9493-0222-42b6-821f-f271e71679ae	\N	en	ICAHD Finland 15 years	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.162895	2026-01-05 11:55:51.162895	icahd-finland-15-years	published	Welcome to celebrate ICAHD Finland's 15th anniversary with Sumud.\n\nThe theme is ICAHD Finland's 15-year history, ICAHD's history in Israel, and forward-looking decolonization and one democratic state.\n\nThere will be two guest talks:\n\nNadia Naser-Najjab is a Senior lecturer in Palestine Studies at the University of Exeter. Her presentation is titled "The Mirage of the two-state Solution - Future Prospects".\n\nJeff Halper is the Director of ICAHD. His lecture is titled "From Genocide in Gaza to One Democratic State".\n\nOther speakers are Veronika Honkasalo (Member of Parliament, Left Alliance), Bruno Jäntti (Founder of ICAHD Finland) and Syksy Räsänen (Chair of ICAHD Finland and Vice-chair of Sumud).\n\nThe event is in English and free of charge.\n\nThe venue is Tekstin talo, Parvisali, in Helsinki and the time is 17:00-20:00 on November 18, 2024.\n\nWelcome!	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-11 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-11 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/event1-2.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
2af1b6a6-cf5c-4cb4-b145-0adda64638cf	\N	en	International Day of Solidarity with Palestine at Bar Alanya, Tampere	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.163406	2026-01-05 11:55:51.163406	international-day-of-solidarity-with-palestine-at-bar-alanya	published	Welcome to mark the International Day of Solidarity with Palestine on November 29th, from 6 to 9 PM at Bar Alanya in Tampere!\n\nThe program includes a musical performance and a Dabke dance workshop by Palestinian artist Tareq Abboushi, along with free time to connect and get to know one another.\n\nWe follow safer space principles. Free entry. Welcome!\n\nAccessibility: the entrance has one small step, otherwise the bar is on the same level. Toilets are unfortunately not wheelchair accessible due to the narrow doors.\n\nThe event is organized by Sumud Tampere.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-21 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-21 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/photo_2024-11-21_15-40-29.jpg	\N	[]	[]	["SUMUD"]
eb5bd9b9-2196-40fc-b7e9-491c0940f7e7	\N	en	Cafe Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.163854	2026-01-05 11:55:51.163854	cafe-palestine-2	published	Monday 25.11. at 5pm-7pm\n\nLocation: Multicultural Centre Saaga, Kouvolankatu 14\n\nWelcome to have a cup of coffee or tea with us. We will be happy to tell you more about SumudKouvola.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-21 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-21 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/467184546_1091208286013702_5802674322589582364_n.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
942a0515-79bd-4390-9162-ddd0f3d421a8	\N	en	Tampere: Academic Boycott of Israel - why, how and why now?	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.164327	2026-01-05 11:55:51.164327	academic-boycott-of-israel-why-how-and-why-now	published	On Thursday 12.12. at 16:15-17:15 we are honored to host a lecture "Academic Boycott of Israel - why, how and why now?" at Metso library (Pirkankatu 2, Tampere), Pihlaja room.\n\nThe Vice Chair of Sumud will hold an English-spoken lecture and Q&A on the history of academic boycott, on Israeli universities' involvement in apartheid and occupation and what academic boycott means in action. Welcome to listen, learn and share insights around the topic!"\n\nThe lecture will be held in English and is open to everyone.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-22 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-22 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/2-4.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
e6fa037e-fa42-40f1-ad56-aaa84fd97c1a	\N	en	Solidarity with Palestine - demonstration in Oulu	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.164796	2026-01-05 11:55:51.164796	solidarity-with-palestine-demonstration-in-oulu	published	⏰ Time: Friday, November 29th at 5:30 PM\n📍 Place: Kauppurin keidas, Oulu\n\nThe genocide against Palestinians in Gaza has been ongoing for over a year. Join us to show solidarity and demand justice for the people of Palestine. The International Day of Solidarity with the Palestinian People has been observed for decades on November 29th, and this year, it is more important than ever.\n\nWe demand that:\n❗️ Finland immediately calls for a permanent ceasefire in Gaza\n❗️ The genocide of Palestinians ends, and Finland supports South Africa's genocide charge at the ICJ\n❗️ The end of arms trade between Finland and Israel\n\nPlease bring only Palestinian, Lebanese or Finnish organizational flags. We do not permit racist (including anti-Semitic or Islamophobic), sexist, or otherwise discriminatory texts and symbols.\n\nOrganizers: Sumud Oulu and Oulu Voices for Palestine	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-22 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-22 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
7a4817d2-a407-4181-b141-2dd90d606253	\N	en	School year cancelled – Yet every child has the right to learn!	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.165752	2026-01-05 11:55:51.165752	school-year-cancelled-yet-every-child-has-the-right-to-learn	published	Welcome to the panel discussion Thursday 21. Nov at 18 to the Pasila library. Discussion in the lobby on the 1st floor. Panel in English.\n\nThere have been a few changes to the panelists from the original ones: Dr. Ata Darwish (Palestine), Tahmine Mehr (Afghanistan), Basam Elfadl (Sudan) and Pazilaiti Simayijiang (East Turkestan). The moderator is Asmaa Abdi.\n\nWelcome also to the demonstration on Saturday 23 November on the topic of Classroom destroyed, School year cancelled at 15-17. We march from Rautatientori a short route to Kansalaistori.\n\nAt Kansalaistori we hear speeches and performers. Speakers Sham and Eibaa Khlouf, Ahmad Hosseini, Mohamed Yousif and Pazilaiti Simayijiang. Performances by Shabana Ahmadzai and Al Tag Girba.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-22 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-22 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/7.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
fd1c1345-ce5b-471b-adf0-6f37448d5198	\N	en	School year cancelled –demonstration in Helsinki	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.166241	2026-01-05 11:55:51.166241	school-year-cancelled-demonstration-in-helsinki	published	🧑🏽‍🏫 School year cancelled -demonstration on Children’s rights week 23rd November 15-17 @ Railway square + short march to Kansalaistori\n\nEducation is under attack around the world, like in Palestine, Sudan, Afganistan and East Turkestan. Children’s right to learn is under a threat and their schoolyears have been partly or fully cancelled.\n\n📢 We call all people who care about children’s rights, families and organizations that work to support children to join our march and demand rights and future for every child living under oppression!\n\nBring signs that demand children’s rights such as the right to safety, protection and learning.\n🏳️ In this demonstration we will not raise any flags, but national/regional flags can be worn on shoulders.\n❌ Racists (including antisemitist or islamophobic), sexist or other discriminative texts and symbols are forbidden.\n\nVaadimme:\n\nOur demands:\n- Finland must advance peace building and children’s protection everywhere in the world\n- Finnish government and political parties must commit to international law and terminate trade relations with states that break international law\n- Finland must protect humanitarian aid in crisis areas and the continuation of the work of UNRWA\n\nThis demonstration is organized by KAMPA (Kasvatusalan ammattilaiset Palestiinan puolesta) in collaboration witth Silti minä nousen ry, Finland with Sudan, Palcif and Sumud.\n\nContact us if you want to support our demo!	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-22 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-22 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
ace8e2e0-a3c1-44cf-93d9-30da960050c5	\N	en	Palestine Movie Night in Kuopio	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.166818	2026-01-05 11:55:51.166818	palestine-movie-night-in-kuopio	published	Palestine Movie Night Friday 22.11. at 19.30 at Kreatorio (Kuninkaankatu 21, KUOPIO) - free entry 🇵🇸\n\nFor Children's Rights Week we will be watching Flying Paper directed by Nitin Sawhney and Roger Hill. 📺\n\nFlying Paper is the uplifting story of Palestinian children in Gaza on a quest to shatter the Guinness World Record for the most kites ever flown. It showcases the creative resilience of these children making and flying kites despite the odds. The film has been co-produced with young Palestinians in Gaza trained by the filmmakers through a youth media program called Voices Beyond Walls. 🇵🇸\n\nAfter the movie we will have an open discussion. You can bring your own snacks and (non alcoholic) drinks, Sumud Kuopio will bring some snacks to share! You can also bring a pillow to get comfortable! ✅\n\nP.S. There is also 'Kuopio punkkaa ja soi' exhibition in the same space so you get to see it, too! 😎	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-22 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-22 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/10.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
f697d7f8-c316-4abb-99f0-e836612243ef	\N	en	Solidarity with Palestine - demonstration in Kuopio	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.167345	2026-01-05 11:55:51.167345	solidarity-with-palestine-demonstration-in-kuopio	published	Friday, November 29th at 6:00 PM\n📍 Market Square, Kuopio\n\nThe genocide against Palestinians in Gaza has been ongoing for over a year. Join us to show solidarity and demand justice for the people of Palestine. The International Day of Solidarity with the Palestinian People has been observed for decades on November 29th, and this year, it is more important than ever.\n\nWe demand that:\n❗️ Finland immediately calls for a permanent ceasefire in Gaza\n❗️ The genocide of Palestinians ends, and Finland supports South Africa's genocide charge at the ICJ\n❗️ The end of arms trade between Finland and Israel\n\nCrafts4Gaza will be there, too. All proceeds go to food aid in Gaza.\n\nPlease bring only Palestinian, Lebanese or Finnish organizational flags. We do not permit racist (including anti-Semitic or Islamophobic), sexist, or otherwise discriminatory texts and symbols.\n\nOrganizers: Sumud and Kuopio for Palestine\n\nProtests are also happening in other cities! Follow the announcements of Palestine groups in your city, or organize your own protest.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-22 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-22 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/2.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
e3de90d7-782e-4a08-8abc-f556106b4946	\N	en	Solidarity with Palestine - demonstration in Helsinki	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.167788	2026-01-05 11:55:51.167788	solidarity-with-palestine-demonstration-in-helsinki	published	Friday, November 29th at 5:00 PM\n📍 Railway Square, Helsinki\n\nThe genocide against Palestinians in Gaza has been ongoing for over a year. Join us to show solidarity and demand justice for the people of Palestine. The International Day of Solidarity with the Palestinian People has been observed for decades on November 29th, and this year, it is more important than ever.\n\nWe demand that:\n❗️ Finland immediately calls for a permanent ceasefire in Gaza\n❗️ The genocide of Palestinians ends, and Finland supports South Africa's genocide charge at the ICJ\n❗️ The end of arms trade between Finland and Israel\n\nPlease bring only Palestinian, Lebanese or Finnish organizational flags. We do not permit racist (including anti-Semitic or Islamophobic), sexist, or otherwise discriminatory texts and symbols.\n\nOrganizers: Sumud – The Finnish Palestine network, Finnish Palestinian community (PALCIF ry), Israeli Committee Against House Demolitions (ICAHD) Finland, Finnish-Arab Friendship Society (FAFS) and Finnish Peace Committee. \n\nProtests are also happening in other cities! Follow the announcements of Palestine groups in your city, or organize your own protest.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-22 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-22 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/2.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
95454f75-973c-4163-a5c1-c17b72476233	\N	en	Justice Not Arms: Finland’s Impact on the Future of Arms Trade – panel in Helsinki	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.168434	2026-01-05 11:55:51.168434	justice-not-arms-finlands-impact-on-the-future-of-arms-trade-panel-in-helsinki	published	Sumud’s Justice Not Arms campaign invites you to its launch event, the panel discussion ”Justice Not Arms: Finland’s Impact on the Future of Arms Trade”, followed by a Q&A.\n\nOur distinguished panelists will discuss the Finnish-Israeli arms trade and how it is imperative for Finland to rethink this relationship to ensure security, justice and the rule of law. The panel will be conducted in Finnish and English.  \n\nPanelists: \n\nMajed Abusalama (Researcher at Tampere University, Sumud Vice Chair of the Board) \n\nRanda Al Dawoudi (Digital Marketing Specialist, Journalist) \n\nJarmo Pykälä (Secretary General at Sadankomitea) \n\nSiiri Kärkkäinen (BDS Finland / Sumud) \n\nModerator: Lili De Paola \n\nVenue: Museum of Photography K1. Address: Kämp Galleria, Mikonkatu 1, 00100 Helsinki \n\nTime: Wednesday 4th of December, at 18-19.30	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-22 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-22 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3-2.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
11dda40a-3a5d-4174-b425-26935a1d3ee1	\N	en	Webinar: Palestine/Israel and Global Accountability	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.16885	2026-01-05 11:55:51.16885	palestine-israel-and-global-accountability-829	published	Join us for a timely webinar, "Palestine/Israel and Global Accountability", featuring esteemed speakers Francesca Albanese, Tamam Abusalama, and Budour Hassan. This webinar will address pivotal challenges related to justice, human rights, and gender, as well as the roles of civil society and foreign states in the pursuit of international accountability in the context of Palestine/Israel.\n\nThere will be time for questions at the end. Register here: https://tuni.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_0A7Zf894RYCPknIEUyAfJA#/registration\n\nFrancesca Albanese is an international lawyer, serving as UN Special Rapporteur on Human Rights in the occupied Palestinian territory since May 2022. A former UN official, she is an affiliate scholar at the Institute for the Study of International Migration at Georgetown University, and a senior advisor on Migration and Forced Displacement for the think tank Arab Renaissance for Democracy and Development (ARDD).\n\nTamam Abusalama is a communication expert born and raised in Jabalia Refugee Camp in the Gaza Strip, currently based in Brussels, Belgium. She is a contributing writer for various online media outlets, including Mondoweiss and Electronic Intifada, where she focuses on personal testimonies and issues related to Palestinian rights, and social justice.\n\nBudour Hassan is Amnesty International’s researcher on Israel and the Occupied Palestinian Territory, currently focusing on Gaza.\n\nThe discussion will be moderated by Ida-Emilia Reini, Sumud board member.\n\nThe webinar is organized by Sumud - The Finnish Palestine Network, and the Finnish Women, Peace and Security Network.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-26 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-26 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/event2.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
245cee46-2bf2-4c63-8288-94b73f8880a5	\N	en	Jyväskylä – Academic Boycott of Israel - why, how and why now?	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.169292	2026-01-05 11:55:51.169292	jyvaskyla-academic-boycott-of-israel-why-how-and-why-now	published	On the International Day of Solidarity with the Palestinian People, Researchers for Palestine invites you to a public lecture with guest speaker Syksy Räsänen on "The Academic Boycott of Israel - why, how and why now?" at the University of Jyväskylä on Friday 29th November at 14:00. In order to get the location of the lecture, please register to the event: https://forms.gle/YL3zYAukw6GDY9D67.\n\nThis is an opportunity to learn more about Israeli universities' involvement in apartheid and occupation and get some information about the demands of the academic boycott.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-28 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-28 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/2-3.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
764619ac-5992-4229-866b-699093cefeea	d2ebb942-6fd9-4c15-a986-56aec057d724	en	Turku – Academic boycott of Israel: why, how and why now?	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.16975	2026-01-05 11:55:51.16975	turku-academic-boycott-of-israel-why-how-and-why-now	published	On Wednesday 27th November 17:00-18:00 Turku with Palestine is organising a public lecture "Academic Boycott of Israel: Why, how and why now?" with Syksy Räsänen.\n\nThe lecture is followed by an optional workshop for those who are interested in discussing the academic boycott of Israel campaign at the University of Turku or other universities based in Turku. The workshop time is from 18:00-19:00.\n\nBoth the lecture and workshop will be takes place in hall Pub126, Publicum building, at University of Turku, Assistentinkatu 7.\n\nWe encourage as many students, members of the student union and groups, researchers, teachers, university administrators to attend this lecture!\n\nIn their last meeting on October 29th, TYY, the University of Turku’s student union made the decision to oppose university-level cooperation with Israel. The fact that the motion sparked heated discussions within and beyond TYY demonstrates the urgent need for clear information about the academic boycott of Israel within the academic community at the University of Turku.\n\nPalestinian civil society's call for the academic boycott of Israel turned 20 years last July. It has been gaining particular traction in the recent months. This lecture will discuss this campaign focusing on the following questions: How is Israeli academia complicity apartheid and genocide? What are the goals of the boycott campaign, and why would it be effective? What are the similarities with and differences from the academic boycott of South Africa and Russia?\n\nThis public lecture is an ideal opportunity for all members of the academic community, including researchers', teachers' and student unions and associations, to learn more and ask questions about the academic boycott and what it entails to an academic, activist and writer who has several years of expertise in Finland-based activism for Palestine as the chair of ICAHD Finland, co-chair of Sumud, and writer of "Israelin Apartheid."\n\nACESSIBILITY INFO:\nThe lecture hall Pub126 is located on the first floor of Publicum. Access for wheelchairs and mobility aids is possible and there is space for a wheelchair in the lecture hall.\nAccess is through the main doors of Publicum from the courtyard. There is a ramp at the main entrance and a button on the right side of the ramp to open the electric doors of the main entrance. Turn left through the main doors and head towards the red lockers. Continue past the red lockers towards the toilet and the glass doors. Hall Pub126 is located behind the glass door behind the toilet, immediately to the left.\n\nThe accessible toilet is located on the first floor lobby near the lecture hall. There are also accessible toilets in the lobbies on the other floors of Publicum.\n\nThere is no induction loop or sound system in the event area. The hall is a small lecture room, where the sound is relatively well reproduced without sound systems.\n\nIf you have any questions about the accessibility of the event, please contact Elina Sutela, elina.sutela@utu.fi	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-28 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-28 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/1-4.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
aabe3842-1ceb-427a-a3a7-7b645f6650b4	\N	en	Helsinki – Academic boycott of Israel: why, how and why now?	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.17044	2026-01-05 11:55:51.17044	helsinki-academic-boycott-of-israel-why-how-and-why-now	published	The lecture will be held at the University of the Arts on 28 November at 17.30 in the fifth floor of the Theatre Academy, room 526, by Syksy Räsänen, Vice President of Sumud. The language of the event will be English.\n\nThe event is an opportunity to learn more about the involvement of Israeli universities in apartheid and occupation, and about the calls for an academic boycott.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-28 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-28 02:00:00	\N	\N	[]	[]	[]
e32c3c2f-682b-48dc-b2c5-0b303c041173	\N	en	Jyväskylä: From apartheid to genocide – the situation in Palestine and Finland	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.171126	2026-01-05 11:55:51.171126	jyvaskyla-from-apartheid-to-genocide-the-situation-in-palestine-and-finland	published	At 17.30 Syksy Räsänen will speak on the topic From apartheid to genocide - the situation in Palestine and Finland. The language of the event will be Finnish.\nLocation: Wolmari-sali, Jyväskylä City Library , Vapaudenkatu 39-41.\n\nIsrael has been committing genocide in Gaza for over a year. Räsänen will talk about the genocide, its background, Finland's and the EU's support for it and the crucial role of civil society.\n\nThe event is organised by the Finnish Peace Committee.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-28 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-28 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
01556124-1157-4d1d-8d93-9dfb6fe3963a	\N	en	Demonstration for Palestine in Jyväskylä	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.171559	2026-01-05 11:55:51.171559	demonstration-for-palestine-in-jyvaskyla	published	Perpetuators of the genocide belongs to the court! Demand justice and freedom for Palestine!\n\nThe demonstration is organized by the Free Palestine JKL collective. The location of the demonstration is Kompassi.\n\nThis demonstration's main speaker will be Syksy Räsänen, vice chair of the Sumud - The Finnish Palestine Network.\n\nGuidelines of safer space are followed in the demonstration. Only flags of Palestine and Lebanon are allowed. You can bring your own placard.\n\nAfter the demo Syksy is attending as a keynote speaker to Keski-Suomen Rauhanpuolustajat's event "Apartheidista kansanmurhaan - Palestiinan tilanne ja Suomi" (in Finnish) at Jyväskylä Main Library's Wolmar-sali. You are welcome to join!	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-28 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-28 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/5.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
7dbbc054-e5d4-4a45-8a9d-dea1e353240a	\N	en	Helsinki: Speeches from and about Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.171988	2026-01-05 11:55:51.171988	helsinki-speeches-from-and-about-palestine	published	Together with Viirus Theatre, the Speech Karaoke Action Group organises an evening dedicated to speeches from and about Palestine. Join us in listening and performing historical, contemporary, political and personal speeches about Palestine. We bring the speeches, you bring your voice!\n\nWe have curated a special list of speeches for this event together with artist Eugenie Touma van der Meulen: https://eugeniecarolina.com/\n\nDuring the event, we will hear speeches from, for example, the UN special rapporteur Francesca Albanese, the late Palestinian-American academic and political activist Edward Said who coined the term Orientalism, and from activists who glued their hands on the statue of Lord Balfour in 2022. We also have speeches from some of the journalists who have been reporting from Gaza this year – Bisan Owda, Hind Khoudary and Motaz Azaiza.\n\nThis special event takes place on The International Day of Solidarity with the Palestinian People. This date is important because, on November 29, 1947, the United Nations proposed creating two states in Palestine. However, only the state of Israel has been established. This date is thus a reminder to the world that the international community has so far failed to guarantee basic human rights to the Palestinian people who never agreed to this division of their country in the first place.\n\nThis year, The International Day of Solidarity comes after a year of remarkable events – and important speeches from, for example, student encampments, the International Criminal Court, and from the Vatican where the pope has demanded investigation into genocide in Gaza.\n\nWarm welcome to everyone! The event is free of charge and you can arrive and leave as you please. Viirus' bar serves refreshments.\n\nFriday 29.11.2024\nFrom 6PM to 10Pm\nViirus Theatre\nVälimerenkatu 14\n00220 Helsinki\n\nYou can find the accessibility information of Viirus here: https://www.viirus.fi/en/theatre/accessibility\n\nMore information about Speech Karaoke https://speechkaraoke.org/	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-28 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-28 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/7-2.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
6d8647f6-4269-495d-9b5f-ecbbf182bc02	\N	en	Hybrid lecture: Israeli activism, Zionism, and the Decolonization of Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.172505	2026-01-05 11:55:51.172505	hybrid-lecture-israeli-activism-zionism-and-the-decolonization-of-palestine	published	The ‘Learning Palestine’ course presents… Guest lecture on ‘Israeli activism, Zionism, and the Decolonization of Palestine’ with Alice Baroni.\n\nLocation: Room A112, Arcanum, University of Turku, Arcanuminkuja 1 and online\nDate and time: Wednesday 4th December, 16:30-18:30\n\nSummary: Drawing from extensive fieldwork in Palestine-Israel, the lecture will provide an overview of the current landscape of Jewish-Israeli activism in Israel, will situate it in the socio-political context of Israeli Zionist society, and will elaborate on the role it can (and cannot) play in the struggle for the decolonization of Palestine.\n\nBio:\nAlice Baroni is a postdoctoral researcher at the University of Turku and expert on settler colonialism in Palestine and settler solidarity.\n\nThe lecture will be followed by a discussion with Anaïs Duong-Pedica (Turku with Palestine activist, PhD researcher at Åbo Akademi University on settler colonialism in Kanaky/New Caledonia) and a Q&A with the audience.\n\nEveryone is welcome, also those who aren’t students at the university.\n\nThe lecture will take place face-to-face at the University of Turku and online.\nIf you’d like to register to attend online, please fill in the registration form to receive a Zoom link: https://link.webropolsurveys.com/S/4E0B426A0E46FCCB\n\nThis event is a collaboration between Turku with Palestine and Researchers for Palestine.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-11-28 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-11-28 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/6-3.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
