469be18b-72c6-451f-818c-5823c88b76f4	\N	en	Helsinki: Candlelight March for Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.174294	2026-01-05 11:55:51.174294	helsinki-candlelight-march-for-palestine	published	Saturday, 14th December at 5 PM\n📍Railway Square, Helsinki\n\nThe genocide carried out by Israel in Palestine has claimed the lives of over 44,000 people. 1.9 million Gazans are internally displaced, with 1.6 million forced to live in tents exposed to floods caused by the rains. Come show your support for Palestinians and remember the victims. This demonstration is a silent march, with no speeches. You are encouraged to wear dark clothing and bring a candle or another light source.\n\nDemands:\n🕯️ Finland must immediately call for a permanent ceasefire in Gaza\n🕯️ The genocide of Palestinians must end; Finland must support South Africa’s genocide case in the ICJ\n🕯️ Finland must end arms trade with Israel\n\nPlease bring only flags of Palestine, Lebanon, or Finnish organizations, along with signs supporting the message of the demonstration. We don't allow racist (including antisemitic or Islamophobic), sexist, or otherwise discriminatory texts and symbols.\n\nOrganizers: Sumud – The Finnish Palestine Network, Finnish Palestinian Community, Finnish-Arab Friendship Society and Finnish Peace Committee	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-12-12 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-12-12 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/5-2.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
608fe98a-dace-4a1c-90f1-17b953860c88	\N	en	Kuopio: Candlelight March for Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.174704	2026-01-05 11:55:51.174704	kuopio-candlelight-march-for-palestine	published	Saturday, 14th December at 5 PM\nHarbour park, Kuopio\n\nThe genocide carried out by Israel in Palestine has claimed the lives of over 44,000 people. 1.9 million Gazans are internally displaced, with 1.6 million forced to live in tents exposed to floods caused by the rains. Come show your support for Palestinians and remember the victims. This demonstration is a silent march, with no speeches. You are encouraged to wear dark clothing and bring a candle or another light source.\n\nDemands:\n\n🕯Finland must immediately call for a permanent ceasefire in Gaza\n\n🕯The genocide of Palestinians must end; Finland must support South Africa's genocide case in the ICJ\n\n🕯Finland must end arms trade with Israel\n\nPlease bring only flags of Palestine, Lebanon, or Finnish organizations, along with signs supporting the message of the demonstration. We don't allow racist (including antisemitic or Islamophobic), sexist, or otherwise discriminatory texts and symbols.\n\nOrganizers: Sumud – The Finnish Palestine Network, Kuopio for Palestine	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-12-12 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-12-12 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/7-3.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
4c779b70-9f29-4b69-afff-8a3177610cb0	\N	en	Oulu: Demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.197085	2026-01-05 11:55:51.197085	oulu-demonstration-2	published	Sumud Oulu and Oulu Voices for Palestine will organise a demonstration on the eve of the Land Day on Saturday, March 29, at 3 p.m. at Kauppurin Keidas in Oulu.\n\nIn 1976, Palestinians organized demonstrations and went on strike because Israel was stealing their land again. As usual, Israel responded with brutal violence, murdering many Palestinians. March 30th was declared the Land Day, which has become a worldwide commemoration of the events of 1976, as well as sumud (steadfastness) and the Palestinians’ continued resistance to Israeli colonialism.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-03-25 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-03-25 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Screenshot-2025-03-25-at-09-18-10-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
772e075c-c8ce-46f8-8f01-783a94f43575	\N	en	Lives as Art, Art as Resistance: A discussion with Shahd Wadi and Laura Junka-Aikio on the Night of Science	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.175105	2026-01-05 11:55:51.175105	lives-as-art-art-as-resistance-a-discussion-with-shahd-wadi-and-laura-junka-aikio-on-the-night-of-science	published	How does the voice of Palestinian women artists resist Israeli occupation and patriarchal hierarchies? How does the telling of life stories become art and an act of resistance?\n\nIn an interview with Professor Laura Junka-Aikio, Palestinian researcher, writer, and curator Shahd Wadi, PhD, discusses the intertwining of art, feminism, and resistance in exile. Join us for a discussion on the Night of Science!\n\n📅 Thursday, January 9, 2025 at 19.00–20.30\n\n📍 Tekstin Talo, Permantosali (Lintulahdenkatu 3, Helsinki) & live-streaming on YouTube on the page of @tekstintalo\n\nThe speakers\n\n✨ Shahd Wadi @shahdwadi is Palestinian among other possibilities, but freedom is mostly Palestinian. She tries to find freedom in what she does, travelling between writing, curation, research, translation, performance and art consultancy. She sought her resistance through her PhD thesis in Feminist Studies at the University of Coimbra in Portugal. Her doctoral thesis has been published as a book entitled “Bodies in a Bundle: Artistic-Life-Stories of Palestinian Women in Exile” (2017).\n\n✨ Laura Junka-Aikio @junkaaikio is a Politics and Cultural Studies scholar and Professor of Northern Politics and Government at the University of Lapland. She has studied Nordic colonialism in Sámi lands as well as the politics and representation of the second Palestinian intifada.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-12-16 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-12-16 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
