ad87707b-b48a-4cf0-aeb2-5483ca9d61c6	\N	en	Oulu: Don't Fund Genocide demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.176325	2026-01-05 11:55:51.176325	oulu-dont-fund-genocide-demonstration	published	Israel has killed tens of thousands of Palestinians since October. In Gaza, people are starving and lack medical care while Israel continues its attacks For over 75 years, Israel has occupied Palestine, displaced Palestinians, and committed numerous human rights violations. End your involvement in Israel's atrocities now and start boycotting!	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2024-12-28 02:00:00	\N	\N	2024-12-28 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/3-1.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
91ad0bf9-8a76-42cb-bf81-2150f03009a0	\N	en	Helsinki: Demonstration Against Genocide!	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.176784	2026-01-05 11:55:51.176784	helsinki-demonstration-against-genocide	published	Demonstration Against Genocide on Monday, 30.12.2024, at 5 PM, in front of the Israeli Embassy, Helsinki.\n\nIsrael's illegal occupation and brutal genocide continue. On Friday, 27.12., Israel struck the Kamal Adwan Hospital, destroying the last operational hospital in northern Gaza. This latest hospital attack is part of Israel's systematic dismantling of Gaza's healthcare system: attacks on hospitals and healthcare workers have been ongoing for months. Deliberate attacks on healthcare facilities and civilians are war crimes.\n\nJoin us to show your support for Palestinians and to demand a ceasefire, an end to the genocide, and the stopping of arms trade between Finland and Israel.\n\nPlease bring only Palestinian, Lebanese, or Finnish organizational flags and signs that align with the message of the protest. We do not tolerate racist (including antisemitism or Islamophobia), sexist, or otherwise discriminatory messages or symbols.\n\nOrganizers: Sumud and Finnish Palestinian Community	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-01-02 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-01-02 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/2.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
6d267ed4-4504-4b0e-a064-1a6e56828c9b	\N	en	Helsinki: Sound of Starvation - March Against the Genocide	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.177492	2026-01-05 11:55:51.177492	helsinki-sound-of-starvation-march-against-the-genocide	published	📍Rautatientori, Helsinki\n⏰Sunday 12th of January at 2 PM\n\nA high risk of famine persists in the Gaza Strip as long as hostilities continue and humanitarian access remains restricted. We demand:\n\n❗️Finland to demand a permanent ceasefire in Gaza\n❗️End the genocide of Palestinians and support South Africa’s genocide charge in the ICJ\n❗️Finland to end arms deals with Israel\n\nOrganisers: Sumud, The Finnish Palestinian Community, Finnish Peace Committee	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-01-14 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-01-14 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/2-1.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
59c95810-037c-4099-8960-51014e4110d7	d50eb48f-e351-4952-b045-4ce3afa2db6d	en	Helsinki: Café Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.177893	2026-01-05 11:55:51.177893	helsinki-cafe-palestine	published	Welcome to the first Café Palestine in 2025 on Sunday 12th January 4.30-7.30pm @ cultural center Oranssi, Suvilahti. 🇵🇸☕️ You can come to warm up in the cafe after the Sounds of Starvation -demo ends. Tea and coffee will be served with some small snacks. You are all warmly welcome and feel free to invite your friends too❤️\n\nThis time we are joined by the team behind the Laki Särmään (Law On Point) citizen initiative, which aims to regulate arms imports to Finland. The team will give us info and tips on how to discuss about this initiative with people. Though arms exports are regulated, there are currently little to no regulations on arms imports, and the state of Finland is indeed a major importer of arms from Israel.\n\nRead more at lakisarmaan.fi, sign the initiative at https://www.kansalaisaloite.fi/fi/aloite/14227 and tell your friends!\n\nAccessibility info:\nOranssi’s entrance, event space and toilets are at street level and are accessible with support devices of all sizes. However, some higher doorway thresholds and sloping ramps may be difficult for people using manual wheelchairs. The toilets are gender-neutral.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-04-28 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-04-28 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/3.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
7a68ce9d-335a-437f-a9cc-ef1f7248fee8	\N	en	Helsinki: Winter sales	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.178463	2026-01-05 11:55:51.178463	helsinki-winter-sales	published	Crafts4gaza together with Sumud Helsinki are co-organising an event at Tekstin talo on Tuesday and Wednesday 14-15 January 2025 from 17-20.\n\nThe programme will include Palestinian stories and poems, as well as craft and banner workshops.\nPalestinian pastries, desserts and hot drinks for sale.\nAs usual, a wide range of products from Crafts4gaza and Sumud merch will be on sale.\n\nThe situation in Gaza is catastrophic and the need for aid is greater than ever!\nFood aid and clean water must continue to be delivered to Gaza and now is a great opportunity for you to come along and support our efforts at our two-day event.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-01-14 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-01-14 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/4.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
fa2f7a4e-d6cc-4b69-8b0d-e37e41abcd56	\N	en	Helsinki: Sumud at Käänne Festival	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.179745	2026-01-05 11:55:51.179745	helsinki-sumud-at-kaanne-festival	published	Welcome to the Käänne Festival to hear about Sumud's activities! KÄÄNNE is a new festival of politics and culture, open to everyone, aiming to change the direction of Finland, burdened by right-wing policies. On Saturday 18 January at 16-18 in Rune Hall, Sumud's activists will talk about Sumud's activities and ongoing campaigns. The language of the event is Finnish.\n\nSumud is an intersectional association working for Palestinian rights. Sumud has quickly become the most important Palestine solidarity organisation in Finland, with branches in several cities. Syksy Räsänen, Vice-Chair of Sumud's Board, talks about Sumud and how to get involved.\n\nJustice Not Arms is Sumud's campaign calling for an end to all arms sales and other military cooperation between Finland and Israel. The campaign aims to stimulate a social debate on the impact of arms trade and to call on political decision-makers to act on behalf of human rights and international law. Right now, the campaign is collecting names for a citizens' initiative on the regulation of defence procurement. Jenni Ahti tells us more about the Justice Not Arms campaign and how to get involved.\n\nBDS Finland is part of the international Palestinian-led Boycott, Divest, Sanctions movement, which aims to cut off political, cultural and economic support from Israel until Israel ends its illegal occupation of Palestine and systematic oppression of Palestinians. Salla Korhonen talks about BDS Finland's ongoing campaigns and boycotts and their impact on human rights.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-01-16 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-01-16 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Kappaleen-teksti.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
