ee61dc7c-3dd1-4579-bd59-cf674c2981be	\N	en	Tampere: The cultural boycott of Israel	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.182106	2026-01-05 11:55:51.182106	tampere-boycott-eurovision	published	Come follow Sumud Tampere’s panel conversation on 8.2.2025. The conversation focuses on the cultural boycott of Israel. The panelists are professionals in the cultural field. The Panel is in english and is held in Teatteri Telakka at 12:30-14:30.\n\nThe panelists are:\n- Musician Tareq Abboushi\n- Filmmaker Hichem Naami\n-Film director Haidi Motola\n\nThe panel is a part of a larger event focusing on boycotting the Eurovision together with @tamperewithpalestine and @palcif48 . We are boycotting Eurovision because Israel is allowed to join despite the ongoing genocide. Eurovision should NOT be encouraging positive PR on Israel.\n\nAccessibility Information:\nEvent is on the third floor. No elevator. The bathrooms are located in the second floor 15 steps down. No accesible bathroom available. Bathrooms are gender neutral.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-01-20 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-01-20 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/3-2.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
a719e78f-f299-4226-93cb-3e9dd147625d	\N	en	Helsinki: Meeting Cafe Salam	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.182519	2026-01-05 11:55:51.182519	helsinki-meeting-cafe-salam	published	Crafts4Gaza, Aseistakieltäytyjäliitto, AKYS and Sumud Helsinki invite you to Meeting Cafe Salam at the Peace Station in Helsinki on Sunday 26.1.2025.\nThe café will be open from 13-18.\n\nThe programme will include discussions and campaign presentations at even hours, including the Law on Point citizens' initiative, the Mask Off Maersk camp in Copenhagen and a presentation on the EU-Israel Association Agreement.\n\nThere will be a Crafts4Gaza Palestine-themed craft sale table, with proceeds going to food aid in northern Gaza. Crafts4Gaza's local team in Northern Gaza will also provide infant formula, clean water and bake bread for local families. You can also come and make your own supporting handicrafts, with materials and guidance provided on the spot.\nAKYS will have an information/sales table at the event, with proceeds going to the Palestinian Medical Relief Society's health work in Gaza.\nSumud Helsinki will also have its own table at the event.\n\nLunch and savoury and sweet treats will be available for sale at the café. Half of the proceeds from the café will go towards keeping the Peace Station running and half towards humanitarian aid in Gaza.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-01-24 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-01-24 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/1-3.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
43b2fcbe-be42-49f7-afc6-55baafa13336	02f9f7fc-d205-4167-ba08-93db60175a1f	en	Helsinki: Café Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.184282	2026-01-05 11:55:51.184282	helsinki-cafe-palestine-2	published	Welcome to February Café Palestine on Sunday 2nd February 5-8pm @ cultural center Oranssi, Suvilahti. Cafe Palestine is organized in collaboration between Sumud Helsinki and Palcif.\n\nTea and coffee will be served with some small snacks. You are all warmly welcome and feel free to invite your friends too\n\nIn February cafe we will sing boycott songs and more familiar Palestine freedom songs led by Palestine Carols Choir! Come sing or listen while enjoying a cup of hot drink and warm atmosphere\n\nAccessibility info:\nOranssi’s entrance, event space and toilets are at street level and are accessible with support devices of all sizes. However, some higher doorway thresholds and sloping ramps may be difficult for people using manual wheelchairs. The toilets are gender-neutral.\n\nمرحبًا بكم في *مقهى فلسطين*لشهر فبراير\n\nيوم الأحد 02-02 من الساعة 5 إلى 8 مساءً\n\nفي :\n\n*Oranssi Cultural Center, Suvilahti\n\n. يتم تنظيم مقهى فلسطين بالتعاون بين **صمود هلسنكي* و PALCIF**الجالية الفلسطينية في فنلندا\n\nسيتم تقديم الشاي والقهوة مع بعض الوجبات الخفيفة.\n\nاهلا وسهلا بالجميع، ولا تترددوا في دعوة أصدقائكم أيضًا.\n\nفي مقهى فلسطين لهذا الشهر فبراير، سنغني أغاني عن مقاطعة الاحتلال وأغاني عن حرية فلسطين بقيادة *جوقة ترانيم فلسطين*! تعالوا للغناء أو الاستماع بينما تستمتعون بكوب من المشروبات الساخنة وأجواء دافئة.\n\n*معلومات الوصول*:\n\nمدخل أورانسي في قاعة الفعاليات.\n\nدورات المياه كلها على مستوى الشارع وهي مهيأة للوصول إليها باستخدام أدوات الدعم من جميع الأحجام.\n\nومع ذلك، قد تكون بعض العتبات المرتفعة عند المداخل والمنحدرات المائلة صعبة للأشخاص الذين يستخدمون الكراسي المتحركة اليدوية.\n\nدورات ا	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-02-01 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-02-01 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Cafe_2.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
dff5d020-6930-4c24-9007-54759e735f53	\N	en	Karkkila: From apartheid to genocide	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.184953	2026-01-05 11:55:51.184953	karkkila-from-apartheid-to-genocide	published	Wednesday 5.2. at 17-19\n\nVenue: cinema Kino Laika\n\nTalk by the Vice President of the Finnish Sumud - Palestine Network and cosmologist Syksy Räsänen. The third edition of Syksy's book Israelin apartheid has recently been published. The book will be available at the event at a low price.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-02-01 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-02-01 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/475558764_9374812209247925_1386686525838056491_n.jpg	\N	[]	[]	[]
c68b7719-18d0-420c-bc89-2004e04a7436	\N	en	Helsinki &amp; online: Strategic campaigning for Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.185361	2026-01-05 11:55:51.185361	helsinki-online-strategic-campaigning-for-palestine	published	We’re excited to host an activist from BDS Sweden for a hands-on workshop on strategic campaigning for Palestine! 🇵🇸✊ This is your chance to gain practical skills, exchange ideas, and strengthen the movement.\n\nWhat: 4-hour workshop\nWhen: February 23rd, 14–18\nWhere: Museum of Impossible Forms (Aallonhalkoja 9L 1, Helsinki) or online\n\nRegister to the workshop on Eventbrite: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/strategic-campaigning-for-palestine-workshop-tickets-1231034620689\nThe Zoom link will also be sent to those who register to the event.\n\nGrassroots groups are often campaigning with limited time and energy. Being strategic helps us make actual change - by thinking things through and analysing our situation first, we can make conscious decisions about the way forward that is most likely to work. A clear plan enables everyone to pull together, predict issues that might arise and make the most of opportunities. Looking ahead means we can plan our capacity realistically, and keep going for the long haul.\n\nJoin us for a workshop on developing our strategic campaigning skills in the fight for a free Palestine!	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-02-03 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-02-03 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/WORKSHOP-ver1-ENG.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
58d80c53-b76d-4ed9-b5b2-ddd67c323571	\N	en	Helsinki &amp; online: Lecture on the BDS Movement	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.185778	2026-01-05 11:55:51.185778	helsinki-online-lecture-on-the-bds-movement	published	We’re thrilled to welcome an activist from BDS Sweden for a powerful and inspiring lecture on the BDS Movement! This is your chance to learn, engage, and be part of an important conversation about justice and solidarity.\n\nWhat: 1,5h lecture and after that an interactive Q&A and discussion.\nWhen: Saturday February 22nd, 14–16.\nWhere: Museum of Impossible Forms (Aallonhalkoja 9L 1, Helsinki) or online.\n\nZoom link: https://helsinki.zoom.us/j/67047065542\n\nSince 1948, Israel has denied Palestinians their fundamental rights, refusing to comply with international law. It maintains a regime of settler colonialism, apartheid and occupation over the Palestinian people. This is only possible because of international support. Governments fail to hold Israel to account, while corporations and institutions across the world help Israel to oppress Palestinians.\n\nBecause those in power refuse to act to stop this injustice, Palestinian civil society has called for a global citizens’ response of solidarity with the Palestinian struggle for freedom, justice and equality.\n\nIn this lecture, we will try to outline some of the ways you can support Palestinian liberation and end apartheid and settler colonialism. From the shopping basket to the ballot box. From home and from work. At universities and in the playing field.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-02-03 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-02-03 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/LECTURE-ver1-ENG.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
de25f83e-cc5d-44cc-918f-553c610da14f	\N	en	Kuopio: Academic boycott of Israel – why, how and why now?	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.186183	2026-01-05 11:55:51.186183	kuopio-academic-boycott-of-israel-why-how-and-why-now	published	On Wednesday 19th of February at 16:00-17:00 we will have a public lecture "Academic Boycott of Israel: why, how & why now" by guest speaker Syksy Räsänen. The lecture will take place at the Snellmania campus in Kuopio, space SN200. The lecture will be in english.\n\nWHAT IS IT ABOUT?🍉\nSyksy Räsänen will talk about the context in which Israeli universities operate and their involvement in apartheid, occupation and genocide. He will go through the Palestinian call for academic boycott, compare it to the cases of Russia and South Africa, and discuss academic freedom.\n\nWHY SHOULD YOU ATTEND?🍉\nIn the past year the student unions HYY, AYY and ArtSU have all accepted their members' initiatives for the academic boycott. Also SYL, the national union of student unions, demands that all finnish universities join the academic boycott of Israeli academic institutions. This includes our university.\n\nThis lecture is a great opportunity for anyone to learn more about these topics, in order to understand the necessity of the academic boycott of Israel. We therefore encourage all students, researchers, teachers, members of the student unions and university administrators to attend this lecture.\n\n❕️DIRECTIONS:\nWhen you enter the Snellmania building from the main doors, take the stairs on the left to the second floor. After your past the second floor doors, turn right. There are lecture spaces with big letters on the doors. SN200 is the first one.\n\n❗️ACCESSIBILITY INFO:\nThe lecture will take place on the second floor of the Snellmania building. There are ramps at the main entrance and a button to open the doors. Elevator to get to the second floor is located under the stairs that are on your left after entering the building. The elevator comes into a lobby space that has a door without an electronic opening. So if coming alone with wheelchair, please notify us beforehand via dm or email, so we will come open the door for you! There is space for a wheelchair in the lecture space. Inva toilet is in the first floor before the stairs.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-02-12 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-02-12 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Screen-Shot-2025-02-12-at-23.11.17.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
9c37ebab-2fe9-4667-a56b-746f245cb80e	\N	en	Helsinki: News from Palestinian refugee camps in Lebanon	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.186594	2026-01-05 11:55:51.186594	helsinki-news-from-palestinian-refugee-camps-in-lebanon	published	On Saturday 15 February at 14:00, AKYS together with Psychologists for Social Responsibility and the Finnish Palestinian Community will organise an event in Helsinki, where Kassem Aina will talk about the situation in Lebanon.\n\nWelcome!	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-02-12 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-02-12 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/1.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
d796f5b3-0112-484a-a1da-b8d326224ce1	\N	en	Turku: Tatreez – Palestinian Embroidery	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.187014	2026-01-05 11:55:51.187014	turku-tatreez-palestinian-embroidery	published	Exhibition at Kirjakahvila, Turku, February 22 – May 18, 2025.\n\nThe "Palestine Wall" at Kirjakahvila will be adorned with tatreez works. Palestinian tatreez embroidery tells stories of history, resilience, and identity. The exhibition features tatreez embroidery pieces and provides information on the historical evolution of this tradition up to the present day, highlighting its significance in preserving Palestinian culture and identity.\n\nThe opening event will take place on Saturday, March 22, at 2 PM, with Nemat Battah performing Palestinian music on the oud.\n\nFollowing the concert, from 3 to 6 PM, there will be a tatreez workshop where participants can try their hand at embroidery. Instructions and threads will be provided on-site, please bring a fabric to embroider on, such as a plain shirt, tablecloth, curtain, pillowcase, pencil case, or tote bag. Linen or cotton is preferred, denim can also work. Avoid very delicate or overly heavy fabrics, such as wool. Kirjakahvila is located at Brinkkala yard, Vanha Suurtori 3, Turku. The gallery is open on weekdays from 12 to 6 PM outside of events. Free entry.\n\nArtists: Nemat Battah, Maya Amer.\n\nCurator: Ida-Emilia Reini	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-02-12 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-02-12 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Screen-Shot-2025-02-12-at-23.41.59.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
1e54bc25-edbd-4f49-b9b2-bab0bf63383c	\N	en	Helsinki: Author interview – Samah Sabawi and Cactus Pear for my Beloved	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.187654	2026-01-05 11:55:51.187654	helsinki-author-interview-samah-sabawi-and-cactus-pear-for-my-beloved	published	Join us for a discussion of memory, history and colonialism between the author, playwright and poet Samah Sabawi from Palestine and Anaïs Duong-Pedica, teacher and researcher from Kanaky/New Caledonia. The event is organised in the central library Oodi (Töölönlahdenkatu 4, Helsinki), 3rd floor, Saarikoski-matto.\n\nSamah Sabawi is originally from Gaza and now lives in Australia. Her new book, Cactus Pear for my Beloved, is a memoir of her family over the past 100 years. It has been described as "a magic lantern and an elegant mosaic and a reclaiming and a reassertion of memory and history".\n\nThe book was born out of Samah's PhD research into memory in the context of generational trauma and exile. She last visited Gaza in July 2023, and much of the landscape described in the book has now been turned to scorched earth.\n\nYet, her book is a story of optimism, and belief in the strength of art, family and community.\n\nThe event is organised by Sumud – The Finnish Palestine Network. The discussion will be held in English.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-02-14 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-02-14 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Screen-Shot-2025-02-14-at-23.16.50.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
9558c85e-9f1e-49ad-906b-d428fd3ac9b3	\N	en	Jyväskylä: Palestine still needs support demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.188069	2026-01-05 11:55:51.188069	jyvaskyla-palestine-still-needs-support-demonstration	published	Israel's recent escalation in breaking the ceasefire agreement reminds us that global attention is still necessary to support Palestine.\n\nThe ceasefire may be shaky because of Israel, but we are not.\n\nWelcome to demonstrate on Thursday 20th of February at 5:00 PM that the work is not over.\n\nGuidelines of safer place are followed at the demonstration\n\nFree Palestine JKL & Sumud Jyväskylä	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-02-18 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-02-18 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Screen-Shot-2025-02-18-at-21.25.54.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
ec449cd9-acbd-4f3e-abca-ef0d74a718a3	\N	en	Tampere: book club	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.188609	2026-01-05 11:55:51.188609	tampere-book-club	published	Welcome to Sumud Tampere book club on Monday 10.3. at 17-19. We will meet in Artteli (Mustanlahdenkatu 22).\nGuest: Palestinian-Korean comic book artist Maryam ”Mellu” Abuzaid-Ryu.\nDiscussion about the book ”Läpileikkaus”.\n\nYou can participate without reading the book. Conversation in Finnish and English as needed.\nNext book club meetings:\n17.4. (Guest TBA)\n26.5. (Irene Zidan, book Isäni appelsiinikukkien maasta.)\n\nThe book club meets at Artteli room Kuulu (1st floor).\n\nAccessibility:\n\nArtteli functions in three floors. There are no stairs to the first floor and there’s a ramp at the front door of the building. The width of the doorway is approximately 180 centimeters at its widest.\nThere are several stairs to the upper floor. The upper floor is accessible also with the chairlift. The doorway of the lobby of the upper floor is 177 centimeters wide. The doorways of the conference room are 88 centimeters wide and their thresholds are approximately one centimeter high. The lower floor of the building is accessible only through the stairs but there are only toilets, though, which can be found in other floors as well.\nThe toilets are gender neutral. On first floor there is an accessible toilet with low threshold. The height of the threshold is approximately two centimeters and the width of the doorway 100 centimeters.\nThere’s no induction loop in the building.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-02-18 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-02-18 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/2.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
