110cfdec-05a2-4c00-87e3-00622b0edcd7	\N	en	Sumud's Palestine Summer School	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.190285	2026-01-05 11:55:51.190285	sumud-summer-school	published	Sumud's Palestine Summer School will be organised on August, 22-24, in Pirkanmaa.\n\nRegistration is now open!\n\nThis year's theme is Take Action!\n\nJoin us in collective learning about Palestine. Freeing this world from genocide, apartheid and occupation, takes concrete action. Learning needed skills together with other like minded people is great way to build capacity for collective action! If you have ever felt powerless during past years or decades, this is your moment to come and cultivate power in supportive, inspiring atmosphere together!\n\nPlease note that the Palestine Summer School is for Sumud members only. Instructions for joining and paying the membership fee on our website.\n\nSumud - The finnish Palestine Network wants to build an intersectional movement for collective justice and liberation from Finland to Palestine.\n\nDate: 22.8.-24.8.2025\nLocation: Pirkanmaa\nPrice: 60€  / 30€ for discount groups (financial aid is available, so please apply even if beyond your price range)\n\nLink to registration: https://cryptpad.fr/form/#/2/form/view/1iqGr+9uNILO0K8PfyD3b4PvFU+6qxaBZpFKAJxPXeg/ \n\nProgramme will be held in English.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-02-20 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-02-20 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/1-1.jpg	\N	[]	[]	[]
d1e6a61a-97aa-4167-94f5-50ab6c55bdad	8c74c1a0-a85d-40be-af2e-c37a5940a991	en	Helsinki: Café Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.190737	2026-01-05 11:55:51.190737	helsinki-cafe-palestine-3	published	Welcome to Café Palestine on Sunday 2nd of March at 5-8pm at Kulttuurikeskus Oranssi in Suvilahti!\n\nCafé Palestine is organized in collaboration between Sumud Helsinki and Palcif.\n\nBefore the café, there will be an onboarding session for the newcomers at 4-5pm. Join us to learn more about Sumud!\n\nDue to the beginning of Ramadan, we will share an Iftar meal together to break the fast in the evening. We will offer soup, coffee, tea and dates. If you can, bring food or snacks to share at the meal.\n\nWe will provide a space for prayer.\n\nOranssi’s entrance, event space and toilets are at street level and are accessible with support devices of all sizes. However, some higher doorway thresholds and sloping ramps may be difficult for people using manual wheelchairs. The toilets are gender-neutral.\n\n-----\n\nأهلا وسهلا بكم في ”مقهى فلسطين” يوم الأحد، 2 مارس، من الساعة 5 إلى 8 مساءً في مركز أورانسي الثقافي.\n\nينظم مقهى فلسطين بالتعاون بين صمود - هلسنكي و الجالية الفلسطينية في فنلندا.\n\nقبل بدء المقهى، ستكون هناك جلسة تعريفية للمشاركين الجدد من الساعة 4 إلى 5 مساءً. انضموا إلينا للتعرف أكثر على صمود!\n\nومع حلول شهر رمضان المبارك يسرنا أن نتشارك في وجبة إفطار معًا.\n\nسنقدم الحساء، القهوة، الشاي والتمر.\n\nإذا كان بإمكانكم الحضور والمشاركة، يرجى إحضار طعام أو وجبات خفيفة للمشاركة خلال الوجبة.\n\nسنوفر مساحة للصلاة.\n\nمعلومات إمكانية الوصول:\nمدخل مركز أورانسي، ومساحة الفعالية، ودورات المياه تقع جميعها على مستوى الشارع وهي مهيأة لاستخدام أجهزة الدعم بجميع الأحجام.\n\nومع ذلك، قد تكون بعض العتبات المرتفعة للأبواب والمنحدرات المائلة صعبة للأشخاص الذين يستخدمون الكراسي المتحركة اليدوية.\nدورات المياه محايدة الجنس.	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-02-25 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-02-25 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/WhatsApp-Image-2025-02-20-at-07.41.42.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
5bcdd5c9-436d-45a1-a325-5d7d503d0272	f845d324-280e-4c38-b9bf-5e8c8940d963	en	Kouvola: Eden is West	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.19138	2026-01-05 11:55:51.19138	kouvola-eden-is-west	published	The film group Edvin invites the SumudKouvola group to watch a film during the Anti-Racism Week; Tue 18.3.2025 at 6pm.\n\nAfter the film, SumudKouvola will organize evening tea and a pin workshop in the theater cafeteria. Free entry. Welcome.\n\nAddress: Kuva-Portti, Kouvolankatu 10, Kouvola)	\N	havu.laasko	havu.laasko	2025-03-17 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-03-17 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/1.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
0b65fc05-5db4-47f8-b6a9-a8deca4c8d9a	\N	en	Movie screening and panel discussion: London Recruits	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.191852	2026-01-05 11:55:51.191852	movie-screening-and-panel-discussion-london-recruits	published	Israeli Apartheid Week is here again! The theme for 2025 is People Power Makes Apartheid History. That happened in South Africa, and it will happen in Palestine.\n\nOn Friday, March 28 at 5:30 p.m. we will screen the South African documentary London Recruits, followed by Q&A with the filmmakers, and a panel discussion. The event will take place at the Cultural Centre Caisa, Kaikukatu 4, Helsinki.\n\nIn the 1960s, things looked bleak for the liberation struggle in South Africa. The leaders of the anti-apartheid struggle were imprisoned, killed or in exile, and the liberation organisation ANC was outlawed. London Recruits tells the true story of activists recruited by the ANC from London to carry out secret missions in South Africa to reinvigorate the liberation struggle. Not all made it back.\n\nAfter the movie, there is Q&A with the filmmakers via Zoom, and a panel discussion about the relation of Israeli and South African apartheid. Discussions are in English and chaired by Syksy Räsänen, the vice-chair of Sumud. The panelists are Ata Darwish, a professor of education from Al-Azhar University in Gaza, now at the faculty of education at the University of Helsinki, and Christopher Wessels, a filmmaker, curator and educator from South Africa currently living in Finland.\n\nTickets €2, €10, €20 or free donation amount. You can buy your ticket beforehand to make sure you’ll have a seat. Mobilepay number 21090, message “London Recruits”.\n\nThe event is co-organised with the Refugee Film Festival.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-03-19 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-03-19 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/WhatsApp-Image-2025-03-19-at-08.41.06-1.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
0a099a50-3050-4607-acf4-5d0805e2ac1e	\N	en	Tatreez workshop in Kuopio	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.192258	2026-01-05 11:55:51.192258	tatreez-workshop-in-kuopio	published	Crafts4Gaza and Vapauden Virkkaajat are organising a tatreez workshop on Wednesday, March 26 at 4-6 p.m. at Cafe Guppo. The workshop is free of charge.\n\nCome and learn the history of tatreez while learning this beautiful traditional Palestinian embroidery! You can bring your own crafting supplies but we have some to get you started.\n\nWelcome!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-03-19 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-03-19 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Screenshot-2025-03-19-at-15-48-03-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
0227cfa4-18b6-4e33-a587-0b5a018eaaa7	\N	en	Land Day Demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.192695	2026-01-05 11:55:51.192695	land-day-demonstration	published	Support the Palestinians right to their land on this march on Saturday, March 29, 2025 commemorating Land Day in Helsinki.  \n\nThe first Land Day march took place in 1976, when the Israelis forcibly took over 20000 dunams (20 km2) of land in the Galilee region, six Palestinian people got killed and hundreds were injured in the protest. Land Day is a national holiday in Palestine and also a protest against the siege of Gaza.\n\nThe occupation is not only killing people but also, land, nature, olive trees, herbs and flowers.\n\nThe Land Day march on March 29 is moving from the Helsinki Railway Square to the Kansalaistori Square. At Kansalaistori we will hear speeches.\n\nAccessibility information: \nThe march moves slowly, there will be a silent block at the end. The march route includes accessibility challenges like curbs and tram tracks. Ask the de-escalator volunteers for assistance if needed. \n\nThe march is organised by  PALCIF, Sumud, AKYS and Rauhanpuolustajat.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-03-24 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-03-24 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Screenshot-2025-03-24-at-10-52-55-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
2791958a-87c7-4cf4-b5d3-68a4cba8a1b4	35877273-e258-4468-9300-8ff8eb5ea820	en	Laki Särmään NYT!	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.193127	2026-01-05 11:55:51.193127	laki-sarmaan-nyt	published	Laki Särmään and Polifa ry are organising an event Laki Särmää NYT! at Tekstin Talo in Helsinki on Tuesday, March 25, at 6-7 p.m.\n\nThe event program includes an introduction to the citizens' initiative Laki Särmään and how to support it. The initiative aims to have war crimes and other human rights violations of international humanitarian law taken into account in defence procurement imported into Finland.\n\nThe citizens' initiative closes on 22 April and requires 50 000 signatures in order to proceed to Parliament. Sign today and join us to hear more!\n\nProgram:\n\n18-18.10 Welcome and intro, Eeva Mäkinen, Founder of POLIFA, PhD researcher in postcolonial political imagination and democracy, University of Lapland\n\n18.10-18.25 Jenna Jauhiainen, Laki Särmään -working group member, What is Laki Särmään?\n\n18.25-18.40 Bruno Jäntti, PhD researcher in EU Middle East foreign policy, democracy and human rights, University of Helsinki and Harvard Fulbright Fellow\n\n18.40-19.00 Open discussion and Q&A	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-03-24 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-03-24 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Screenshot-2025-03-24-at-11-04-29-Instagram-1.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
df9c405b-110f-43d3-ae2d-d079dbf79b3d	\N	en	Lecture: Israel, apartheid and genocide	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.193572	2026-01-05 11:55:51.193572	lecture-israel-apartheid-and-genocide	published	Sumud Kouvola is organising a lecture on Israel, apartheid and genocide on Thursday, May 15, at 5:30–7 p.m. at the auditorium of the Kouvola main library. The guest of the lecture is Frank Johansson, the Executive Director of Amnesty International's Finnish section.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-03-24 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-03-24 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Kouvola-1.jpg	\N	[]	[]	[]
12cf0098-78f6-48e0-b22e-5f81d4d9ff31	\N	en	Cafe Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.194038	2026-01-05 11:55:51.194038	cafe-palestine-3	published	Welcome to the pre-Eid Café Palestine on Sunday, March 30, at 5-8 p.m. at Kulttuurikeskus Oranssi in Suvilahti (address Kaasutehtaankatu 1)!\n\nThe program starts with Students for Palestines info for new people. Student! Did you know that you and your student friends have a role in the liberation of Palestine? You can be the change maker in your own university and demand genocide free teaching!\n\nThe program also includes news from Denmark and planning for future actions.\n\nBring a piece of extra cardboard, there will also be a sign making corner! We offer tea, coffee and some snacks and information on Sumud's ongoing campaigns.\n\nSee you Sunday March 30 for an easy going apartheid free evening!\n\nAccessibility info:\nOranssi's entrance, event space and toilets are at street level and are accessible with support devices of all sizes. However, some higher doorway thresholds and sloping ramps may be difficult for people using manual wheelchairs. The toilets are gender-neutral.\n\nمرحبًا بكم في مقهى فلسطين قبل العيد\nبتاريخ 30.3 من الساعة 17:00 إلى 20:00\n\nيبدأ البرنامج بمعلومات عن طلاب من أجل فلسطين للوافدين الجدد.\nطالب! هل كنت تعلم أنك وأصدقاؤك الطلاب تلعبون دورًا في تحرير فلسطين؟ يمكنك أن تكون صانع التغيير في جامعتك والمطالبة بتعليم خالٍ من الإبادة الجماعية\n\nيشمل البرنامج أيضًا آخر الأخبار من الدنمارك والتخطيط للإجراءات المستقبلية.\nأحضر قطعة إضافية من الكرتون بما يصلح ليكون لافتة، سيكون هناك ركن لصناعة اللافتات! نقدم شاي، قهوة، وبعض الوجبات الخفيفة ومعلومات عن حملات صمود الحالية\n\nنراكم في 30.3 لقضاء أمسية مريحة خالية من الفصل العنصري\n\nمعلومات الوصول\nمدخل أورانسي، ومساحة الحدث، ودورات المياه كلها تقع على مستوى الشارع ويمكن الوصول إليها باستخدام الأجهزة الداعمة بجميع الأحجام. ومع ذلك، قد تكون بعض العتبات العالية والممرات المائلة صعبة للأشخاص الذين يستخدمون الكراسي اليدوية. دورات المياه محايدة من حيث الجنس	\N	su