12de7547-4e60-41d8-bff9-f639214ebbd8	\N	en	Fundraiser	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.196273	2026-01-05 11:55:51.196273	fundraiser	published	Sumud Jyväskylä and Free Palestine JKL will organise a fundraiser on Tuesday, March 25, from 4 p.m. to 7 p.m. at Bar Vakiopaine (Kauppakatu 6, Jyväskylä).\n\nBring your friends and family along and come check out what you can get for donating to Palestine. The fundraiser will focus on supporting multiple small campaigns of the donor's choosing that can reach the people on the ground.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-03-25 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-03-25 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Screenshot-2025-03-25-at-08-43-02-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
f0a2fd03-8720-4168-bdac-aa47da946ff1	\N	en	Kuopio: Demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.196683	2026-01-05 11:55:51.196683	kuopio-demonstration	published	KPO for Palestine and Students for Palestine Kuopio will organise a demonstration on Land Day on Sunday, March 30, at 12 p.m. at the Kuopio Market Square.\n\nLand Day is a Palestinian annual day of remembrance on March 30th, commemorating the 1976 protest and strike against Israeli government land expropriations. The occupying force used brutal violence against the demonstrators. The day symbolizes Palestinians' defense of their land and rights, as well as resistance against the occupation. Come show your support and solidarity with the Palestinian people!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-03-25 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-03-25 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Screenshot-2025-03-25-at-09-08-17-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
042ec2f8-3b1e-4258-974a-338544bfd204	\N	en	Lecture: Academic Boycott of Israel - Why, How and Why Now?	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.19813	2026-01-05 11:55:51.19813	lecture-academic-boycott-of-israel-why-how-and-why-now	published	The Equity team and GloseNet of the University of Jyväskylä will organise a guest lecture "Academic Boycott of Israel - Why, How and Why Now?" on Friday, April 25, at 2-4:30 p.m. The event will be held at the first floor lobby of Ruusupuisto campus at the University of Jyväskylä (Alvar Aallon katu 9) and the lecture will also be streamed online.\n\nThe guest speaker is Syksy Räsänen, the co-chair of Sumud, former chair of ICAHD Finland, and author of Israelin Apartheid. The lecture will address the involvement of Israeli universities in colonialism, apartheid and occupation. It will discuss the background and demands of the academic boycott call, and compare it to the academic boycotts of South Africa and Russia.\n\nThe lecture will be followed by a round table discussion with researchers and activists sharing their diverse perspectives.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-04-02 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-04-02 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Untitled-design-1.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
fbb7a1b5-777e-42e6-9ff0-bf58f79ffd1b	\N	en	Tampere: Books and Encounters	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.198576	2026-01-05 11:55:51.198576	tampere-books-and-encounters	published	Sumud Tampere and KSL Study Centre will organise a book club on Thursday, April 17, at 5-6:45 p.m. in Kumppanuustalo Artteli (Mustanlahdenkatu 22, Tampere). The topic of the book club and an open discussion is identity and art. The guest of the event is Noora Dadu who is a Palestinian-Finnish actor, writer and the chair of Sumud.\n\nWe will be discussing Noora Dadu's book Minun Palestiinani ja Fail (2022). The questions revolve around art and identity: can art reach beyond international conflicts and identity?\n\nWarm welcome to participate in the discussion and to learn new things in a good company. You don't need to read the book to participate as the focus is on having an open discussion around the topics. Discussion is in Finnish and English as needed.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-04-07 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-04-07 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/WhatsApp-Image-2025-04-02-at-17.51.521.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
4d99a6d0-109e-498b-97d5-db20c6594763	\N	en	Oulu: Demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.198984	2026-01-05 11:55:51.198984	oulu-demonstration-3	published	Sumud Oulu and Oulu Voices for Palestine will organise a demonstration for the Laki Särmään citizens' inititative on Saturday, April 12, at 3 p.m. at Kauppurin Keidas in Oulu.\n\nPalestinian suffering continues while the world watches. While Finland has long been promoting international regulation for arms exports, no regulations exist that would ensure responsible arms import that takes human rights into consideration. This has to change! Join us this Saturday to demand an end to the genocide and an end to arms trade with Israel!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-04-09 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-04-09 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Screenshot-2025-04-09-at-09-25-41-Kaikki-julkaisut-•-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
6d094ed7-e1b3-424c-9f0b-b1fc88f43e5c	\N	en	Sumud's annual meeting	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.199386	2026-01-05 11:55:51.199386	sumuds-annual-meeting	published	Sumud's annual meeting will be held on Tuesday, June 10, at 6 pm in Helsinki. Register for the annual meeting here.\n\nSumud is looking for new board members from all over Finland!\n\nThe Sumud Board consists of up to 12 members and a chair. Board term lasts for two years and half of the board is elected yearly. Sumud aims to have at least one third of its board members be Palestinian.\n\nBoard members play an active role in the activities of the organization and work in collaboration with other volunteers, staff and partners of the organization. Board position is a volunteer position, for which there is no financial compensation.\n\nAfter the official part of the meeting, there will be some side programme. You can find the registration form and information about running for the board here. You can find the registration for an online board introduction meeting on May 14, at 5 pm through the same form.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-04-14 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-04-14 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/5.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
