22dd4202-eefd-4302-bda6-fd8f1e25e044	\N	en	Tampere: Vappu march	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.203366	2026-01-05 11:55:51.203366	tampere-vappu-march	published	Tampere's May Day march will have a Palestine block organized together with Tampere with Palestine and Sumud Tampere. We demand justice to the workers and students of Palestine who are suffering under the occupation and genocide. We will gather at Laikunlava's skate ramp at 10:30, the actual march starts at 11:15! Join us to keep our voices heard!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-04-28 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-04-28 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Screenshot-2025-04-28-at-15-47-15-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
f4470204-2c11-485e-8944-b66c6ec109bb	\N	en	Helsinki: Mother's Day march for Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.203801	2026-01-05 11:55:51.203801	helsinki-mothers-day-march-for-palestine	published	Doula-akatemia, KAMPA, Finnish-Arab Friendship Society, Palestinian Community in Finland and Health Workers for Palestine Finland will organise a march for Palestine on the eve of Mother’s Day, on Saturday, May 10. The march will gather at 3 pm in Central Railway Square and move to the Parliament House via Mikonkatu, Aleksanterinkatu and Mannerheimintie. The march will remember parents who have lost their children and children who have lost their parents, demonstrate and demand safe childbirth and protection of families in Gaza.\n\nYou may bring Mother’s Day flowers to the march in memory of mothers who have died. Children and adults can carry stuffed animals in their arms. Those who wish can carry small bodies wrapped in white cloth (e.g., a doll or a bundle of clothes). We will lay all of these on the steps of the Parliament House at the end of the march.\n\nAt the Parliament House, there will be a few speeches, singing together, and small activities for children. The event will end no later than 5 pm.\n\nWe are looking forward to seeing individuals and organizations working for and with pregnant and birthing people and families with babies to show their solidarity for Palestinians.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-04-30 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-04-30 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Screenshot-2025-04-30-at-09-00-26-Kaikki-julkaisut-•-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
5171572f-69c7-49d0-89d0-5817a02dbd61	54b74d30-06a9-4bc4-a2f5-5759d71062ce	en	Hämeenlinna: Vappu	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.204226	2026-01-05 11:55:51.204226	hameenlinna-vappu	published	HAMK Students for Palestine, Hämeenlinna with Palestine and Sumud Hämeenlinna are taking part in the Mayday Workers Event on Thursday, May 1. On May Day you can support the Palestinian cause in Hämeenlinna in the following ways:\n\nJoin the 12:30 Mayday march leaving from Eino Leinon puisto (park next to the Häme castle). Bring your own Palestine flag/sign or borrow one from us at the Hämeenlinna's market square between 12:00 and 12:15.\n\nVisit our table at the Hämeenlinna market square starting from 1pm, where you can buy beautiful Crafts4Gaza and Sumud merch and get information on Palestine action.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-04-30 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-04-30 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Screenshot-2025-04-30-at-09-23-28-Kaikki-julkaisut-•-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
d338bc24-41e9-4f84-af19-41f1c9ecd111	\N	en	Helsinki: Candle for mothers and children in Gaza	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.20527	2026-01-05 11:55:51.20527	helsinki-candle-for-mothers-and-children-in-gaza	published	UNICEF Finland and the Women’s Association Unioni will organize a candle-lighting and moment of silence for the mothers and children of Gaza, on Mother’s Day, Sunday, May 11, at 7:30 pm on the steps of the Finnish Parliament House in Helsinki. Bring your own candle (e.g. a grave candle or similar non-draining candle).\nYou can also light a candle at home and share a photo at 7:30 p.m. on Mother’s Day evening with the hashtag #PeaceForGaza (#RauhaGazaan).	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-04-30 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-04-30 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Screenshot-2025-04-30-at-09-50-59-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
161cba72-4ed9-4c32-a969-6f6b680f4670	\N	en	Activestills – Documenting life, death and resistance in Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.205658	2026-01-05 11:55:51.205658	activestills-documenting-life-death-and-resistance-in-palestine	published	Photo: Mohammed Zaanoun, Gaza city, 2023\n\nExhibition of the Activestills photography collective at the Finnish Museum of Photography (The Cable Factory, Kaapeliaukio 3, Helsinki) 9.5.–31.8.2025. Since 2005, the Activestills photography collective has been documenting Israeli colonial violence and Palestinian resistance.\n\nThis exhibition presents a selection of the collective’s work of over two decades, focusing on the attacks on Gaza and the current genocide, the ongoing ethnic cleansing across Palestine as well as the remains of villages depopulated by Zionist forces in 1948. Activestills’ work strives to portray Palestinians not only as victims but as individuals and a people with diverse political agency in their struggle. Activestills perceives its work of documenting and archiving as a form of narrative reclamation and resistance to the colonial practice of destruction, control, co-option, appropriation and erasure against Palestinian lives and voices.\n\nFind out more about the exhibition and the opening hours and tickets of the museum here.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-04-30 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-04-30 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/4.-MOHAMMED-ZAANOUN_GAZA-CITY_2023.jpg	\N	[]	[]	[]
2843cc95-d11d-4ea3-82f4-f749b15a0aac	\N	en	Jyväskylä: May Day March	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.206036	2026-01-05 11:55:51.206036	jyvaskyla-may-day-march	published	Join the Palestine block organised by Free Palestine JKL and Sumud Jyväskylä at the May Day March in Jyväskylä on May 1! The Palestine block gathers at 11 am at Järjestöjentalo (Ilmarisenkatu), and the march begins at 11:30 am. The event continues at 12 pm at Lounaispuisto with a May Day celebration.\n\nThe march is organized by SAK Jyväskylän alueen paikallisjärjestö ry.  More info here.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-04-30 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-04-30 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Screenshot-2025-04-30-at-12-58-33-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
7b1a3bbf-07b8-41c8-9fb6-0aec9a9c0f35	\N	en	Photo exhibition: Traces of the Nakba	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.206406	2026-01-05 11:55:51.206406	photo-exhibition-traces-of-the-nakba	published	Photo: Ahmad Al-Bazz\n\nTraces of the Nakba photo exhibition on 6.5.–31.5.2025 at the Helinä Rautavaara Museum (Shopping centre Entresse, Siltakatu 11, Espoo).\n\nDuring the Nakba, or ‘catastrophe’ in English, which culminated in 1948, Palestinians were forced out of their homes and villages to make way for the inhabitants of the newly established state of Israel. This kind of violent displacement is considered ethnic cleansing.\n\nBetween 2021 and 2023, Palestinian photographer Ahmad Al-Bazz (b. 1993) visited dozens of Palestinian towns emptied by early Zionist settlers since the Nakba. With his photographs, Al-Bazz aims to reestablish 1948 as the entry point into discussing Palestine-Israel. A selection of these photographs is now exhibited in Helinä Rautavaara Museum.\n\nThe Nakba of 1948 must still be spoken in the present tense, as long as forcible transfer and displacement still threaten the Palestinians who survived the early stages of ethnic cleansing, most of whom live under Israeli military rule. Similarly, colonialism is often seen only as a part of history, although its mechanisms continue to influence the world around us, including our lives.\n\nThe exhibition is produced in collaboration with Ahmad Al-Bazz. Entry to the museum is free.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-05-05 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-05-05 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Nakban-jaljilla-markkinointikuva-2.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
6b67cbca-4cd4-4edf-a949-f7443ee090a1	\N	en	Discussion at the World Village Festival	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.206788	2026-01-05 11:55:51.206788	discussion-at-the-world-village-festival	published	How to achieve a rights-based and decolonised peace in Palestine-Israel? What does this require in practice? What is Finland’s role in this work? Sumud hosts a panel discussion about Finland’s role in advancing a just and sustainable future in Palestine-Israel at the World Village Festival, on May 24, at 7:05–7:30 p.m.\n\nThe panel discussion deconstructs Western-centric models of peace mediation and explores the meaning of decolonisation. The panelists are Noora Dadu, Chair of Sumud – the Finnish Palestine Network, Georgia Gerike, founding member of Nahlieli – Jews for Justice in Palestine and Ilaria Tucci, board member of the European Peace Research Association. The discussion is moderated by Lili De Paola, coordinator of Sumud – The Finnish Palestine Network.\n\nThe discussion is in English. The programme can be followed on the festival’s Speaker’s Stage in Tiivistämö or via streaming on the festival’s website. Free admission!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-05-05 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-05-05 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/World-Village-Festival-2025.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
eb9cb1d2-bf64-4f76-8672-aa0a96f47693	b73f5a4f-65e2-4f04-9a77-e642ba9bb022	en	Helsinki: Amnesty's weekly demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.207167	2026-01-05 11:55:51.207167	helsinki-amnestyn-viikoittainen-mielenosoitus	published	Amnesty International Finland is organizing a demonstration on Fridays at 8:30-9 am at the Israeli Embassy at the corner of Simonkatu and Yrjönkatu in Helsinki.\n\nThe protests demand that Israel:\n\nstops the genocide of Palestinians in Gaza\n\nagrees and commits to a lasting ceasefire\n\nstops the actions that have led to the rapid deterioration of living conditions for Palestinians in Gaza\n\nensures that Palestinians in Gaza receive urgently needed humanitarian aid\n\nYou can get ready-made signs at the demonstration. Please do not bring flags. No racist, sexist or discriminatory texts or symbols will be allowed.\n\nSee you at the demonstration on Fridays!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-05-05 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-05-05 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Screenshot-2025-05-05-at-15-41-19-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
1a128c2d-41a7-49e6-b016-e6e323076432	\N	en	EUROVISIOFF – Boycott Eurovision event	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.207573	2026-01-05 11:55:51.207573	eurovisioff-boycott-eurovision-event	published	Do you also desire for an option to celebrate without supporting the genocidal entities that Yle or EBU seems to keep on supporting?! grab your keffieh, matching Palestinian flag outfit and lets have an Intifada on the dancefloor\n\nWelcome to Sumud's eurovisiOFF- Eurovision boycott event on 17.5. saturday 7pm in Tekniikan museo, Energiasali (Viikintie 1 B, Helsinki).\n\nTickets: Only at door 10e/20e or pay what you can.\n\nDespite the demands of hundreds of thousands of people, EBU has decided to maintain the participation of Israel in Eurovision. In solidarity with Palestine, join the BDS call to Boycott Eurovision and join one of the multiple boycott events.\n\nFor EurovisioOFF we've gathered heart filling lineup for ya'll:\n\n19:00 DOORS\n20 Opening speech\n20:10 Eugenie (Poetry) (PS/NL/FIN)\n20:45 MAKAN (Live) (PS/SK/FI)\n21:30 Al Hurriya Team - from Gaza (Dabke workshop + performance) (PS)\n22 Baher of Finland (IRQ) & Ritni Tears (SÁ) (Drag)\n22:45-23:30 Bashar Murad (Live) (PS)\n23:30-00 Chanting & singing together w/ Sirin & Eugenie + RoR drums\n00-03 Yalla collective (live/DJ) (SWANA)\n01:30- 03 Trabelsi (DJ) (FI/TUN)\n\nIn addition to our decoration-team's cozy atmosphere, we have beautiful artwork-prints by\nRand Hamdallah in collaboration with local Palestinian kids!\n\nTo keep our belly happy, Lebanese food is served by Shawarma station!\n\nCalming our thirst and mind, enjoy tea served at the tea-hut\n\nFor our hungry eyes; cinema by Hichem Naami - ”the finnish Sumud” documentary.\n\nGet your gear of the year from Crafts4Gaza- table.\n\nDrinks served at the bar – BYOB\n\nThis evening is an invitation to show support and solidarity to the Palestinian people and it’s resistance. Gather, recharge and celebrate together in a genocide free party!\nMORE about community guidelines shared at the door, make sure to take a moment to reflect on them! "Push the fun, not the boundaries!"\n\nAccessibility info: Beautiful big and warmed up venue 'Energia-sali'\nAddress: Viikintie 1 B, Helsinki. **Follow the EurovisiOFF-arrows from the road to the venue**\n\nEntrance, space and bathrooms are wheelchair accesible. (Entrance doorstep 5cm, with a ramp. Door 98cm wide. Acessible bathroom door 90cm wide. Stair lift available to enter the main area.)\nThe event is hosted in english.\nThere's a tea/calm-space. Please respect the rooms tranquility <3\nBring your earplugs, while there's also some available at the venue.\nNo hearing aid/induktiosilmukka unfortunately.\n\nIf you or people around you need help, we have awareness and security guards for your safety and needs! Don't hesitate to ask help, we're here for you <3\n\nHope to gather with you all under this energy of resilient and liberative joy!	\N	admin_mohammad	admin_mohammad	2025-05-05 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-05-05 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Untitled.jpg	\N	["Cultural events"]	[]	["SUMUD"]
ff9c943e-6176-4434-8f14-91e70eb806b9	\N	en	Helsinki: Document screening	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.208219	2026-01-05 11:55:51.208219	helsinki-document-screening	published	Welcome to watch the document Syytettynä Israel and discuss about the situation in Palestine with Pertti Pesonen, the director of the document. The event is organised by Finnish-Arab Friendship Society and Palestinian Community in Finland and will take place on Wednesday, May 14, at 6 pm at Oranssi, Kaasutehtaankatu 1, Helsinki.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-05-06 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-05-06 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Nimeton.jpg	\N	[]	[]	[]
e23df525-6076-4be8-8c88-327eddeccefd	\N	en	Exhibition: Hand-by-Hand	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.208588	2026-01-05 11:55:51.208588	exhibition-hand-by-hand	published	Image: Lara Salous\n\nLara Salous' exhibition Hand-by-Hand on 26.4.-17.5. in Titanik gallery in Itäinen Rantakatu 8, Turku.\n\nRamallah-based Palestinian artist and designer Lara Salous tells the story of a land constantly repaired by the careful threading of relations between generations, knowledges, and with the territory. Palestine appears in Salous’ work as layered with life, culture passed over hand-by-hand, and a proud companionship with the land and its environment. Hand-by-Hand presents Lara Salous’ research of wool-spinning traditions in Palestine, born from her close collaboration with Bedouin shepherd communities. \n\nMore information about the exhibition here.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-05-06 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-05-06 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/image-x-website-1536x1024-1.jpg	\N	[]	[]	[]
b67269d9-9473-47a4-99e1-aa4e172b5f46	\N	en	Tampere: Nakba Day demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.208947	2026-01-05 11:55:51.208947	tampere-nakba-day-demonstration	published	Tampere with Palestine and Sumud Tampere will organise a demonstration on the day of Nakba, on Thursday May 15. The demonstration march will start from Sorin aukio at 6 pm.\n\nOn May 15, it will be 77 years since the Nakba – the catastrophe that the zionists carried out, during which over 700,000 Palestinians were violently displaced from their homes – happened and continued into the occupation of Palestine and to the genocide we see Israel committing now. Join us in solidarity with Palestine to demand the end of the occupation!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-05-07 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-05-07 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Screenshot-2025-05-07-at-14-52-55-Sumud-Tampere-صمود-تامبيري-@sumud.tampere-•-Instagram-kuvat-ja-videot.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
357b6719-ff4f-49df-aa75-82973c2ffc1d	\N	en	Helsinki: Nakba Day protest	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.20931	2026-01-05 11:55:51.20931	helsinki-nakba-day-protest	published	Nakba Day protest on Thursday, May 15, at the main building of the University of Helsinki (Fabianinkatu 33, Helsinki) from 10 a.m. onwards. The protest is organised by Students for Palestine Finland, Students for Palestine Aalto University, Researchers for Palestine and SOCO.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-05-07 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-05-07 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Nayttokuva-67.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
139d382a-7e49-4203-912f-9751775d8e2b	\N	en	Activestills Live-opastus	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.227712	2026-01-05 11:55:51.227712	activestills-live-opastus	published	Suomen valokuvataiteen museo järjestää tiistaina 5.8. klo 16–17 virtuaaliopastuksen museon vaihtuviin näyttelyihin.\n\nVirtuaaliopastus järjestetään Instagramin livelähetyksenä. Seurataksesi opastusta kirjaudu Instagramiin tunnuksillasi ja saavu Valokuvataiteen museon Instagram-sivulle (@valokuvamuseo). Liveä voi seurata tietokoneella selaimen kautta, tai puhelimelle ladatun sovelluksen kautta.\n\nOpastus on mahdollista katsoa vain suorana lähetyksenä, eikä siitä jää Instagramiin tallennetta myöhemmin katsottavaksi.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-07-22 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-07-22 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Nayttokuva-2025-07-22-125829.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
2c6bafd3-17c9-4588-9bb5-f8db279d320f	\N	en	Jyväskylä: Food is not a weapon -demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.209699	2026-01-05 11:55:51.209699	jyvaskyla-food-is-not-a-weapon-demonstration	published	Free Palestine Jyväskylä and Sumud Jyväskylä will organise a Food is not a weapon -demonstration on Nakba Day, Thursday, May 15 at 5 pm at Kompassi Jyväskylä.\n\nMay 15th marks Nakba Day. In 1948 Palestinians were forcibly displaced. What began as a catastrophe has never ended. Hundreds of thousands of Palestinians were deprived of their right to their own homes then, and today, generations later, the Palestinians of Gaza face famine and bombardment under a total blockade.\n\nIsrael prevents food, water and medicine from entering Gaza. Since 2008, Israel has controlled Gaza’s food supply. Since March 2025, the blockade has been complete: Civilians are starving to death. In over 15 months of Israel's assault, more than 50, 000 Palestinians have been murdered, including tens of thousands of children. Nearly two million have been displaced into starvation, rubble, and despair.\n\nThis is not only history repeating itself – this is a violent continuation of it. Join us in remembering the beginning of the Palestinian displacement on Thursday, May 15, at Kompassi, Jyväskylä.\n\nEnd the genocide. End the blockade. End the occupation.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-05-12 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-05-12 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Screenshot-2025-05-12-at-15-44-14-Kaikki-julkaisut-•-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
0ddb6260-43f7-4140-8dec-ba235161681d	\N	en	Helsinki: Demonstration on the 77th Anniversary of the Palestinian Nakba	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.210078	2026-01-05 11:55:51.210078	helsinki-demonstration-on-the-77th-anniversary-of-the-palestinian-nakba	published	Suomen Rauhanpuolustajat, the Finnish-Arab Friendship Society, the Palestinian Community in Finland and Sumud – the Finnish Palestine Network will organise a demonstration on the 77th anniversary of the Palestinian Nakba on Thursday, May 15, at 5 pm, at the Helsinki Railway Square.\n\n“Nakba” (the catastrophe) refers to the ethnic cleansing of Palestinians in 1948. It involved violent displacement, confiscation of land and property, the systematic destruction of Palestinian society, and the suppression of culture, identity, political rights, and national aspirations.\n\nJoin us to show solidarity with the Palestinian people and to remember the tragedy of the Nakba, which led to the forcible displacement of over 750,000 Palestinians and the death of tens of thousands.\n\nWe will not forget – we will not give up. Palestine will live forever!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-05-12 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-05-12 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Screenshot-2025-05-12-at-16-17-53-Kaikki-julkaisut-•-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
08fe9b2b-4d83-45e7-a89a-849f7a536683	\N	en	Oulu: Falastinvision watch party	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.210458	2026-01-05 11:55:51.210458	oulu-falastinvision-watch-party	published	Sumud Oulu and Pohjois-Pohjanmaan Vasemmistonuoret are organising a Falastinvision watch party in Koskelankylän Walo, Ketjutie 3, Oulu on Saturday, May 17, from 9 pm onwards (Finland time)!\n\nFalastinvision is a genocide-free song contest that supports Palestine and creates a great alternative for those boycotting Eurovision. Please see their web page for more information!\n\nWe are going to watch Falastinvision final together! This is a great opportunity to find great artists to listen to and make new friends with others who support the cause.\n\nLIST OF THINGS TO BRING WITH YOU:\n\nsnacks (preferably vegan)\n\ndrinks (no alcohol)\n\npillows, blankets and plushies to create more comfortable watching experience\n\nJBL speakers (they can be linked to each other and placed across the room for better audio quality)\n\nIn Koskelankylän Walo there will be a lot of space for dancing as well!\n\nUnfortunately there is no wheelchair ramp outside.\n\nWe follow the safer space principles and the event is suitable for children.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-05-13 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-05-13 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Screenshot-2025-05-13-at-09-13-03-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
103d2da7-32a0-4e46-98d2-ea8893fbfb20	\N	en	Turku: Arna's Children documentary screening	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.210834	2026-01-05 11:55:51.210834	turku-arnas-children-documentary-screening	published	Turku with Palestine will screen the documentary Arna’s Children by Juliano Mer Khamis on the Nakba Day, Thursday, May 15th at 7 pm at Kirjakahvila in Turku. The documentary is in Arabic and Hebrew with English Subtitles. Free entry.\n\nSYNOPSIS:\nArna Mer Khamis was a legendary Israeli activist against the occupation. Born Jewish, she married a Palestinian and spent her life campaigning for human rights. In the Jenin refugee camp, Arna opened a theatre where, with her son Juliano, she taught children to express themselves through art. When Arna died of cancer in 1995, the theater ultimately did not survive. Five years later, Juliano, one of the region's leading actors, returns to discover what happened to "Arna's Children". Shifting in time, his film juxtaposes the young boys with the militants and martyrs they become, exposing the horror of young lives trapped by the circumstances of Israeli occupation.\n\nBefore the screening, join us for a hangout and solidarity crafting, including drawing, nail art, face paint and letter writing, starting at 5 pm on the Brinkkala yard (Vanha Suurtori 3).	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-05-13 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-05-13 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Screenshot-2025-05-13-at-09-39-11-Kaikki-julkaisut-•-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
069d1837-9da0-473e-82aa-a15b2d2e7e35	\N	en	A Vote of No Confidence - Mass protest	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.211196	2026-01-05 11:55:51.211196	a-vote-of-no-confidence-mass-protest	published	A Vote of No Confidence mass protest on Sunday, May 18, in Helsinki, Kuopio and Oulu will bring together people who oppose the dismantling of the welfare state, tax cuts for the wealthy, discriminatory policies, and the erosion of fundamental rights. With this protest, we express our concern about the direction in which the government is taking Finland – and there are many of us who are worried. The mass protest will take place at the Helsinki Senat Square, Kuopio's Market Square and Oulu's Rotuaari Square at 2 pm.\n\nBehind the mass protest is a diverse group of Finns: teachers, doctors, social workers, researchers, artists, students, parents, and professionals from many fields. The event follows safer space principles and accessibility is ensured. The march is peaceful, family-friendly, and open to all.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-05-13 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-05-13 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/ENG-NO-CONFIDENCE-social-media-post-scaled.jpg	\N	[]	[]	[]
