245c5d7a-87a0-49c1-9d2b-b0ac3a9b2f7e	\N	en	Tampere: Human chain	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.213673	2026-01-05 11:55:51.213673	tampere-human-chain	published	Tampere with Palestine will organise a human chain demo on Friday, May 30, at 6 p.m., at Hämeensilta, Tampere. We demand the end of the occupation on Palestine and an immediate end to the further displacement and genocide of palestinians in Gaza. We demand Finland and other governments to act now.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-05-26 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-05-26 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Screenshot-2025-05-26-at-14-38-14-Kaikki-julkaisut-•-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
62646ec7-f986-4909-b6bb-aac1cd243d38	\N	en	Hämeenlinna: Demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.214054	2026-01-05 11:55:51.214054	hameenlinna-demonstration	published	Welcome to demonstrate against the ongoing enabling of the genocide on Thursday May 29th at 6 pm. We'll meet at Hämeenlinna's marketsquare. The demonstration is organised by HAMK Students for Palestine and Hämeenlinna with Palestine.\n\nIf you want, you can bring a demonstration sign or a piece of fabric with a fitting statement. We'll stand still and chant a few chants, no speeches this time.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-05-28 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-05-28 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Screenshot-2025-05-28-at-09-22-14-Kaikki-julkaisut-•-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
29800f43-cc1b-4cde-b1f7-069de1d9dbcf	\N	en	Hämeenlinna: Quiet Book Club	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.214443	2026-01-05 11:55:51.214443	hameenlinna-quiet-book-club	published	Sumud Hämeenlinna, Hämeenlinna with Palestine ja HAMK Students for Palestine will organise a Palestine themed quiet book club on Sunday, June 8, from 12 pm to 2 pm at the Hämeenlinna City Library. Bring your own book with the theme of the book club or choose one of the books we will bring that are listed in the pictures and below.\n\nWe will meet in front of the Hämeenlinna city library at 12 pm sharp where we will move 12:05 to the park next to the library or indoors. The indoor space is under 500 meters away and it is unfortunately not a wheelchair accessible place and the bathroom is quite small.\n\nFirst we make a small introduction round, get seated and read the books quietly for half an hour. Then we talk about the books we just started. Lastly we will schedule a new quiet book club meeting.\n\nBooks that we have for Sunday:\n\nREWORLDING RAMALLAH: Short Science Fiction Stories from P4lestine\n\nMaryam Abuzaid-Ryu - Läpileikkaus\n\nLived Resistance Against the War on Palestinian Children (edited by Heidi Morrison)\n\nPalestiinalaisia runoja -runokokoelma\n\nBooks that we might get for Sunday:\n\nRashid Khalidi - The Hundred Years' War on Palestine\n\nRashid Khalidi - Palestiina\n\nEdward W. Said - Orientalismi\n\nUmayya Abu-Hanna - Nurinkurin\n\nUmayya Abu-Hanna - Alienin silmin\n\nNoora Dadu - Minun Palestiinani ja Fail\n\nHuzama Habayeb - Before the Queen Falls Asleep\n\nAdania Shibli - Sivuseikka\n\nSusan Abulhawa - Rakkaudetonta maailmaa vastaan\n\nSusan Abulhawa - Sininen välissä taivaan ja veden\n\nSusan Abulhawa - Jeninin aamut	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-06-05 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-06-05 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/Screenshot-2025-06-05-at-13-08-16-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
4ae21185-a4c2-460f-8e8d-009b6a698e95	\N	en	Helsinki: Café Palestine Picnic	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.21481	2026-01-05 11:55:51.21481	helsinki-cafe-palestine-picnic	published	Sumud Helsinki welcomes all to a summer Café Palestine-picnic on Wednesday, June 11, at 5-8 pm in Mustikkamaa!\n\nThis time we will gather to talk, hang out (in the sun), get energy from the community and as usually plan for coming events.\n\nThe picnic area is in Mustikkamaa, if you walk over the bridge from Kalasatama, it's directly to your right 200m towards the Zoo café. You can also get there by bus 16, it's the end stop.\n\nBring a blanket, water and some snacks if you want, we will have something small, fruits and tea/coffee. \n\nIf the weather is bad, we will instead have an indoor picnic in Museum of Impossible Forms at Aallonhalkoja 9 L1, you get there with tram 13 or 10 min walk from Kalasatama metro. \n\nThere are accessible toilets close to the picnic place, but to get up on the grass can be tricky with wheels. The Museum of Impossible Forms is accessible and has an accessible toilet.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-06-05 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-06-05 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/summer-picnic.jpg	\N	[]	[]	[]
