decf00b9-4fc6-4086-884e-8beb195da696	\N	en	Helsinki: Human Chain Against Genocide	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.218906	2026-01-05 11:55:51.218906	helsinki-human-chain-against-genocide	published	Palestinian Community in Finland, Finnish-Arab Friendship Society and Sumud Helsinki will organise a human chain against genocide on Monday, June 16, 5 pm at by City Center in Kaivokatu, Helsinki.\n\nJoin us in forming a human chain against the genocide in Gaza. Let’s stand together and show that we do not accept violence, occupation, or apartheid!\n\nPolice will be present to ensure safety at the event. Racist, sexist, or otherwise discriminatory symbols and slogans are not allowed. De-escalators will be present — you can approach them if you feel unsafe or have any concerns.\n\nThere will also be chant leaders guiding collective slogans — but you are equally welcome to protest silently if that feels more natural. Every way of being present is valuable.\n\nFeel free to bring signs, friends, and your voice for justice!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-06-16 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-06-16 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/WhatsApp-Image-2025-06-13-at-10.50.35.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
25675355-436f-4511-a67e-57a4a5f6245b	\N	en	Webinar: Trade unions and solidarity	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.219295	2026-01-05 11:55:51.219295	webinar-trade-unions-and-solidarity	published	JHL will organise a webinar on trade unions and solidarity on Wednesday, June 18, at 5-7 pm.\n\nWhat role did the trade unions play in the dismantling of apartheid in South Africa? What is trade union solidarity like in 2025?\n\nSpeakers in the webinar: professor Tapio Bergholm, activist and researcher Majed Abusalama and the head of Fagforbundet's international unit Hanna-Mari Anttila-Kvåle.\n\nZoom-link for the webinar:\nhttps://jhl.zoom.us/j/62248820599	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-06-17 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-06-17 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/AyLiikeJaSolidaarisuustoiminta.jpg	\N	[]	[]	[]
50cbd741-01ed-4798-bab9-f27706696ac3	\N	en	Short Film Screening: Queer Cinema 4 Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.219646	2026-01-05 11:55:51.219646	short-film-screening-queer-cinema-4-palestine	published	Queercinema4palestine is a screening organized by Sumud – the Finnish Palestine Network, in solidarity with the global movement for Palestinian liberation. This event challenges the harmful “pinkwashing” narrative used to justify Israel’s genocide and ethnic cleansing of Palestinians. The film screening takes place on Monday, June 23, at 7:30 pm at Elokuvateatteri Orion, Eerikinkatu 15, Helsinki.\n\nThrough a powerful selection of short films by queer, Palestinian, and allied filmmakers, we highlight art’s crucial role in resistance and the fight for freedom.\n\nBy screening these films, we stand in solidarity with Palestinian queer and trans communities enduring ongoing violence and erasure. This screening is a call to action – against pinkwashing, against colonial violence, and for the liberation of Palestine. Let us use our collective voices to refuse complicity and demand justice.\n\nYou can purchase an optional ticket of your choosing from the theater from the following options: 5 euros, 12 euros and 20 euros. You may also simply ask for a free ticket from the counter. Additionally, you may donate an amount of your choosing to Sumud.\n\nRead more and buy the tickets here.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-06-18 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-06-18 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/Screenshot-2025-06-18-at-11-42-23-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
