15318936-59b9-4e2c-901b-0f5b691182ad	8a5d73b1-65b3-4cdd-906e-ec450c2b1c14	en	Hyvinkää: Demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.234594	2026-01-05 11:55:51.234594	hyvinkaa-mielenilmaus	published	Free Palestine Hyvinkää organises a candlelight march for Palestine on Tuesday, September 16 at 6 pm. The march will start from the old church of Hyvinkää (Uudenmaankatu 13) and ends at the library square (Torikatu 5).\n\nAt the library we will hold a memorial service for the children killed in the Gaza genocide and we will lay candles and toys in their memory, so you can bring these with you if possible.\n\nDark clothing recommended.\nThe route of the march is about 700m and is accessible.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-08-27 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-08-27 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Screenshot-2025-08-27-at-15-22-38-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
583ec5f7-357f-4a65-b889-c8c95de5ac14	3f206004-4b33-4268-b7a0-e0c85646d919	en	Helsinki: Evening of Experimental Theatre	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.234968	2026-01-05 11:55:51.234968	helsinki-kokeellisen-teatterin-iltama	published	Evening of experimental theatre organised by the Pahateatteri on Thursday, September 11, at 6 pm at Studio Magito, Suvilahti (Kaasutehtaankatu 1, Helsinki).\n\nExperimentation, exploration, community, and play. Cryptic symbolism, risk-taking, the unfinished and the polished. Live music, dancing, something to eat, and something to drink. Artist interviews, lively chatter, friends – old and new – and an early autumn evening still shimmering with the warmth of summer, at least in spirit.\n\nAll this – and much more – is what Paha Theatre’s new event concept: An Evening of Experimental Theatre, is made of. Throughout the night, audiences will witness 12 different experimental short performances in a club-like setting, created by over 20 artists. Adding to the atmosphere, we’ll have live music played by the brilliant band Mauno, and DJ Ilmari will keep the party going with a dance set at the end of the night. The event’s host will act as a guide and friend, leading the audience through the evening, helping to clarify and deepen the experience. Between performances, the audience will get a rare chance to peek behind the curtain of a traditional theatre experience through direct Q&A sessions and discussions with the creators, led by the host.\n\nIn addition to the artistic content, the evening focuses on creating a laid-back space and atmosphere to have a relaxed and cozy evening together. During performances, doors will be closed to ensure focus – however, the audience is free to move around the space: change seats and perspectives, bring their own snacks and drinks, or purchase them at the venue. During the band and DJ sets, the main entrance will remain open. The evening begins at 18:00 and ends around midnight. A detailed schedule will be announced closer to the event.\n\nThis evening also aims to raise awareness and funds for an ongoing, urgent and vital human rights struggle. Half of all proceeds from the event will be donated to Sumud, the Finnish Palestine Network. Sumud is an intersectional organization working to end Israel's apartheid, occupation, and colonialism, and to promote the human and political rights of Palestinians.\n\nAn Evening of Experimental Theatre is not just a collection of performances. It is a collective experience that invites everyone interested in experimental performing arts and shared values to become part of a community formed by performers and audience members – at least for one night.\n\nTICKETS:\n€20 Standard ticket\n€12 Discount ticket (students, unemployed, pensioners, military service)\n€30 Support ticket\n€4 Solidarity ticket\n(The solidarity tickets are reserved for those who would otherwise be unable to attend due to financial reasons. Limited amount of tickets. Request for Discount Code : pahateatteri@gmail.com)\n\nTickets go on sale on Fri 15.8. at 12:00! Tickets are on sale here.\n\nPerformers: Katariina Broman, Inka Holm, Miika Hukka, Inari Kolehmainen, Roope Kovalainen, Pauliina Kuusisto, Kim Lamminen, Malviina Lehtinen, Vilma Liikkanen, Sebastian Lindström, Lintu Lover, Eero Löövi, Vilma Mankonen, Maisa Mansikka, Eetu Edu Nieminen, Anni Porspakka, Kalle Rissanen, Onni Salmenkivi, Aapo Savisaari, Oona Toivola, Laura Tyyskä, Jerry Uusi-Mikkola, Oona Virolainen and Ville Vuorikoski.\n\nArtistic director: Edu Nieminen\n\nProduction Team: Malviina Lehtinen, Siiri Lehtinen, Eetu Edu Nieminen, Anna Oesch, Irina Ritvanen, Laura Tyyskä and Oona Virolainen.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-08-27 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-08-27 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Screenshot-2025-08-27-at-15-30-40-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
