1057f4bf-a5e6-483b-a8c8-a124569d8910	fbb4bc84-ec9a-4c8a-a1c6-f88353946ca7	en	Helsinki: Rauhan säveliä Concert Series	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.243087	2026-01-05 11:55:51.243087	helsinki-rauhan-savelia-konserttisarja	published	Rauhan säveliä concert series for peace work in October on Sundays (October 5, 12, 19 and 26) at 6 pm in Suomenlinna Church.\n\nIn cooperation with:\nTuomiokirkko seurakunta\nSumud ry\nThe event is supported by the City of Helsinki\nPoster for the concert by Juulia Niiniranta\n\nThe event will include a fundraiser, the proceeds of which will be donated to Sumud.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-09-10 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-09-10 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/rauhan-savelia.jpg	\N	[]	[]	[]
810eea09-7acb-4f25-aac7-57f446857315	ee0a32f2-3af3-431a-a1dc-c8d8af10a9eb	en	Jyväskylä: Palestine cultural event	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.236001	2026-01-05 11:55:51.236001	jyvaskyla-palestiina-kulttuuritapahtuma	published	Free Palestine JKL -collective and Sumud Jyväskylä will organize a Palestine culture event on Wednesday, September 10, at 4-10 pm, at Alakulttuuritalo Kramsu. The event will raise money for Gaza and spread awareness on Palestine.\n\nThere will be all kinds of fun activities, performers and food. Crafts4Gaza, multi-instrumentalist Tareq Abboushi and the singing group Soraääni will be present at the event. In addition, as part of the event, there will also be a dance workshop, where you can dance Dabke, as well movie screenings and an exhibition. Additionally our second-hand clothes fundraiser will make a comeback\n\nTeijän Keittio will be serving vegan food and Dj Am i? will be playing music at the event. Free entry!\n\nCrafts4Gaza takes only cash, Teijän keittiö takes mobilepay and cash options.\n\nAccessibility: Alakulttuuritalo Kramsu’s indoors are not accessible. In front of the main doors are stairs. Indoors after the main doors there’s no high thresholds. There’s no Inva-WC indoors. For more precise information, check Kramsu’s website.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-08-27 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-08-27 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Screenshot-2025-09-08-at-10-08-14-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
ee34c821-21b9-4224-a908-f1276e78c989	a8b38ed7-f58b-4766-add5-d0f81f3361d1	en	Tampere: Manifesto 25 exhibition	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.236389	2026-01-05 11:55:51.236389	tampere-manifesto-25-nayttely	published	Photo: Jana Výborná-Turunen\n\nJana Výborná-Turunen's Manifesto 25 exhibition on 9.8.-14.9. at Culture House Laikku in Tampere.\n\nJana Výborná-Turunen's Manifesto 25 - Textile and Costume Sculptures for Peace, opening at Laikku's Gallery, explores the theme of peace as a protest against the militarisation of the world. The exhibition consists of two parts: the older Manifesto 03 collection and new works that respond to current conflicts, such as the situations in Gaza and Ukraine. The works are symbolic costume and textile sculptures that use meaningful materials: the exhibition includes an image with the names of civilians murdered in Gaza, projected on a carpet of a Jewish family killed in a concentration camp.\n\nRead more on the Laikku website.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-08-27 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-08-27 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/jana.jpg	\N	[]	[]	[]
c3a87b5a-5019-4e63-b252-dc311d1ba5a3	bcb27d78-15e7-42b3-80a6-21c1735d5805	en	Espoo: Palestinian culture event at the Kolibrí Festival	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.236773	2026-01-05 11:55:51.236773	espoo-kolibri-festivaali	published	Kampa Collective will organise a Palestinian culture event Atamanaa at the Kolibrí Festival on Saturday, September 13 at 12 noon at Sello Library in Espoo.\n\nDiscover Palestinian culture at Kolibrí Festivaali! Join us for a lively day in this playground, full of songs, games, poems, and traditional dances. Kampa Kollektiivi wishes to keep Palestinian culture alive through this engaging activity.\n\nNoor Assad (PAL-FI) will teach us songs, poems and games, while Moe (PAL) will lead us through the most common steps of dabke dance, accompanied by dancers from the Finnish dabke group, Al Huriya. Don't miss out on this moving experience, hoping for a world where all children can play in peace.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-08-27 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-08-27 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Screenshot-2025-08-27-at-16-24-16-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
10787a3c-b4fc-4286-980f-927fb3f35226	da401e70-84d9-41e9-8d7a-69380ecd0cbb	en	Helsinki: hospital protests	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.237173	2026-01-05 11:55:51.237173	helsinki-sairaalamielenosoitukset	published	Health for Palestine Finland organises hospital protests by health professionals Monday 8 September from 12 to 13 and Tuesday 9 September from 16:30 to 17:30 . The demonstrations will take place at the Meilahti hospital campus, in front of the main doors of the Tornis Hospital.\n\nThe genocide of Palestinians by the Israeli occupation regime continues to escalate. The complete destruction of northern Gaza has begun. Every morning we read about the night terrors that people are experiencing. Many are unable to move to areas that, despite the occupier's promises of security, continue to be the fate of many Palestinians. The blockade of Gaza has not been lifted and the international media has not been allowed access. The health situation remains disastrous. Starvation leads to daily deaths. Health infrastructure is being destroyed. Direct attacks on hospitals are taking place, killing health workers, students, patients, relatives and journalists.\n\nAs professionals and students in the field of health and social services, we want to show once again our unwavering support for the Palestinians, and demand action with all the authority of our position from the Finnish state, its institutions and its citizens. We want concrete action, not empty talk. The genocide and occupation must end. The conditions for a dignified life must be restored in Gaza. We encourage all our colleagues to join us in the fight for justice! We also welcome supportive protesters.\n\nHealth and social work clothes are welcome on protesters. Feel free to bring your own sign. The demonstration will be quiet - we will not shout slogans or make any noise that might disturb patient work. Racist, sexist or otherwise discriminatory symbols or behaviour are not permitted. Please bring a Palestinian flag if you wish. To keep the focus on the Palestinian situation, please do not bring other flags.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-09-08 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-09-08 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Screenshot-2025-09-08-at-10-50-40-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
795fd3e9-8732-4dcd-897b-8adbd62627dd	b54b7200-34d3-43f0-94f4-27862fac6167	en	Helsinki: Demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.237581	2026-01-05 11:55:51.237581	helsinki-mielenosoitus-5	published	Global Sumud Flotilla, Palcif and Sumud will organise an All Eyes on the Global Sumud Flotilla protest on Wednesday, September 10, at 3-5 pm at Parliament stairs.\n\nThis is the right moment to call on parliamentarians to ensure the safety of the Finnish delegation, a safe humanitarian corridor, and an end to the illegal siege.\n\nWe have two performances confirmed by pro-Palestinian singers. Fatim Diarra from the Greens will join us to speak. One speech will also be delivered by our group.\n\nOn the same day, at 2:00 PM, Parliament will be discussing the Laki Saarmaan initiative. This gives us an important opportunity to gather more people, raise our voices, and increase the pressure.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-09-08 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-09-08 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Screenshot-2025-09-08-at-11-17-11-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
77b1065a-397b-45a6-99b3-a2ac350461cb	\N	en	Helsinki: Students for Palestine's Newcomers' evening	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.23801	2026-01-05 11:55:51.23801	helsinki-students-for-palestines-newcomers-evening	published	Students for Palestine will organise a newcomers' evening on Monday, September 8, at 6-8 pm at Ulrika, Leppäsuonkatu 11, Helsinki.\n\nStudent! Join the fight towards academic boycott of Israel and the liberation of Palestine! During the event you'll get info of the movement and way's you can be a part of the struggle! Join and make the students' voices even more heard	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-09-08 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-09-08 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Screenshot-2025-09-08-at-10-59-20-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
06a277b7-0e43-45a7-b1b3-34f99a774e59	\N	en	Espoo: Aalto Students for Palestine's Newcomers' Event	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.23839	2026-01-05 11:55:51.23839	espoo-aalto-students-for-palestinen-uusien-ilta	published	Aalto Students for Palestine will organise a newcomers meeting on Thursday, September 11, at 4-6 pm in Väre, Aalto.\n\nCome and find out about the movement, previous campaigns and what have been doing recently to demand actions and accountability from our university. You can find a space here to get to know old and new members, find different ways to get involved and bring your own ideas to the table. No prior experience needed, come and learn more.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-09-08 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-09-08 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Screenshot-2025-09-08-at-11-41-19-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
3f0f91b4-e9ad-45ce-b8d0-1f03262bee4f	\N	en	Turku: Granny Squares for Gaza Events	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.238768	2026-01-05 11:55:51.238768	turku-granny-squares-for-gaza-events	published	Granny Squares for Gaza children is a community art project organised by Turku with Palestine that aims to honor the victims of the ongoing genocide in Gaza, by creating a powerful visual of the extent of lost lives. The official number of palestinian children martyred since October 2023 is estimated to be around 20 000, with many more still missing under the rubble. One single square represents 10 children murdered by Israel.\n\nThe community art installation will be exposed as part of Community Point Mustikka's 20 years anniversary art exhibition from 8th to 12th September. The exhibition opening is on Monday 8th at 5pm, and at the same time there will be the possibility to join the project by participating in the workshop held in the same space. Address: Kardinaalinkatu 3 P 151, Halinen.\n\nThe same week, the installation will be exhibited during the Koroisten Kyläjuhlat (Koroinen Café, Koroistentie 2) on Saturday 13th and Sunday 14th September. On both days will be possible to participate in our workshop from 12 to 3pm.\n\nBoth events will be featuring plenty of art, music and activities, so show up and enjoy the sense of community!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-09-08 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-09-08 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Screenshot-2025-09-08-at-11-50-12-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
8b27717d-dde0-46a4-974e-035dc7585dde	a55b34d2-4b86-4baf-863f-43e3764d3664	en	Helsinki: Book Talks on Global Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.239151	2026-01-05 11:55:51.239151	helsinki-book-talks-on-global-palestine	published	The Finnish Institute in the Middle East (FIME) will organise a series of Book Talks on Global Palestine. The first talk will take place on Thursday, September 11, at 4:15-5:30 pm on Zoom.\n\nIn this Thursday's online Book Talk on Global Palestine dr Mark Griffiths talks about the notorious Checkpoint 300, the highly securitized border facility between occupied Bethlehem and Jerusalem, as a stark symbol of Israeli colonialism. More information about the Book Talk and dr Mark Griffiths’ new book and the registration link can be found on the FIME website. Remember to register by Wednesday (10.9.)!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-09-08 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-09-08 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Screenshot-2025-09-08-at-13-21-20-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
96096436-825f-4f10-a5c6-5d237306f8a0	9dd3d922-48a2-498a-b2d4-d6c648b09de3	en	Tampere: Film Screening	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.239824	2026-01-05 11:55:51.239824	tampere-elokuvanaytos	published	Tampere with Palestine and Sumud Tampere will organise a screening of the documentary Doctors Under Attack on Monday, September 22 at 5 pm in Linna (University Library) room K103 at Kalevantie 5, Tampere.\n\nAfter the screening there will be a hosted Q&A session to discuss the documentary, the current situation in Gaza and Palestine, and ways to take action.\n\nThis event will be in English.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-09-08 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-09-08 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Screenshot-2025-09-08-at-13-46-23-Instagram.png	["Sunlight streams through the dense canopy of a lush green forest, casting long shadows on the ground covered in vibrant vegetation. Tall trees with straight trunks reach upward, creating a serene and tranquil atmosphere.", "Poster for an event titled \\"SUMUD TAMPERE: Foragers (Palestine, 2022)\\" featuring a movie screening and discussion on environmental justice. Date: 19.3.2024, Time: 17:00-19:30, Location: Tampere University, Linna, K103. Background shows a woman and abstract art.", "A poster for the film screening of \\"Tale of the Three Jewels\\" (Palestine, 1995). The event is on 27.03 from 6-9pm at Publics, Helsinki. The poster features a photo of a person holding a necklace, with film strip and wave designs in the background.", "A person wearing a white headscarf stands on rocky terrain with a walking stick and a leafy branch in hand, facing a smoldering, burnt landscape with some smoke rising and sparse vegetation in the background.", "A large crowd of protestors is gathered in winter clothing, holding various signs with messages like \\"NEVER AGAIN FOR ANYONE,\\" \\"CEASEFIRE NOW,\\" and \\"APARTHEID HISTORIAAN!\\" Some flags are also visible among the protestors.", "A large contemporary hospital building labeled \\"La Fe Hospital Universitari i Politècnic\\" with a long, white exterior, multiple windows, and several parked cars in the foreground. Leafless trees line the area, and modern residential buildings are visible in the background.", "Front view of the Panthéon in Paris, featuring its grand neoclassical facade with six Corinthian columns supporting a pediment. The large dome is a notable feature of the structure. Tourists are seen gathered at the entrance on a sunny day with a clear blue sky.", "A row of outdoor dog kennels with metal fences houses several dogs, standing or sitting inside. The kennels are attached to a building made of concrete blocks. The grassy area in front is partially in shadow with some leaves visible in the foreground.", "A person wearing traditional attire stands in a barren landscape, holding sticks in both hands. Smoke rises from small fires around them, and hills with scattered trees are visible in the background under a hazy sky.", "A logo features a stylized, leafy tree in green encircled by a broken, red ring. The text \\"Suomen Palestiina-verkosto\\" curves around the right side of the circle.", "I'm unable to view the image you uploaded. Could you describe it to me?.", "Image not available.", "A young woman, draped in a checkered scarf, rides on someone's shoulders during a protest. She holds a flag as part of the large crowd, where people carry colorful flags and signs on a sunny day.", "Black background with text announcing a demonstration for \\"Justice for Gaza!\\" on 03.11.2024 at 2:30 PM in Helsinki, Railway Square. The design features a symmetrical, colorful pixel art pattern in the center.", "A person with curly hair wearing a black \\"Free Palestine\\" T-shirt stands in front of a detailed, patterned tapestry. They have a calm expression and are facing the camera.", "A black T-shirt hangs on a wire hanger against a textured pink wall. The shirt features a small white graphic printed on the chest.", "A size chart for T-shirts listing sizes 1 to 8XL. The chart shows half width and length in centimeters for each size, from 30 cm width, 43 cm length for size 1, to 78 cm width, 87 cm length for size 8XL.", "A woman with long brown hair stands with her hands on her hips. She wears a graphic t-shirt, blue jeans, and a patterned shawl over her shoulders. The background is a light blue, textured wall.", "A beige T-shirt with a black and white abstract design hangs on a wire hanger against a textured pink wall.", "A blue T-shirt hangs on a wire hanger against a textured pink wall. The shirt features a graphic of a white sail and black lines with the text \\"LIBERATION FOR ALL!.", "A person with bright red lipstick stands confidently with hands on hips, wearing a blue T-shirt and patterned jeans in front of a detailed patterned rug.", "Three people stand against a red wall, showcasing casual clothing. Text above reads, \\"Check out our collection! T-shirts, longsleeves, sweatshirts, hoodies, tote bags.\\" They wear different graphic tops and accessories.", "A person wearing a headscarf and sunglasses holds a small green squash. They wear a gray sweater with bold text and a graphic of a watermelon slice. They stand against a weathered blue wall with an arched opening in the background.", "A person wearing a beige headscarf, sunglasses, and a sweatshirt with text, holds a small green squash near their head. They stand against a blue wall with an arched doorway in the background.", "A person in a white sweatshirt with a bold design, paired with tie-dye jeans, stands confidently in a tunnel with blue graffiti walls. They hold a green fruit and wear sunglasses on their head.", "A gray sweatshirt hanging on a hook against a textured red wall. It features bold, distorted black text reading \\"END THE OCCUPATION\\" with slices of watermelon incorporated into the design. Arabic text is also present.", "Size chart for a dress with measurements in cm: Sizes range from 4-6 to 5XL. \\"Width\\" and \\"Length\\" measurements are given for each size: 4-6 (39, 52) to 5XL (78, 90). A dress icon is shown on the left.", "A person with curly hair, wearing a black T-shirt with text calling to end occupation, stands against a pink textured wall. They hold a beige tote bag and have a serious expression.", "A young person with long brown hair stands outdoors on rocky terrain. Wearing a white T-shirt with text and watermelon graphics, they look towards the camera with a neutral expression. The background features rocks and greenery.", "A person with long hair is wearing a white t-shirt with black text and red watermelon graphics. They are standing on rocky terrain with greenery in the background. The weather appears mild and overcast.", "A person with curly dark hair stands against a pink wall, wearing a black T-shirt with text and watermelon graphics that read \\"End the Occupation\\" in English and Arabic. They are holding a light pink tote bag.", "Three people stand against a reddish wall, modeling casual clothing. The text in Finnish promotes products like T-shirts, long-sleeves, sweatshirts, hoodies, and bags, with preorder and delivery information provided.", "A person wearing a black t-shirt with a red flower design stands outdoors against a rocky background. They have a neutral expression and are wearing a beige headscarf. The letter \\"A2\\" is prominently printed in red on the shirt.", "A person wearing a black sweatshirt with text \\"End the Occupation\\" in English and Arabic stands in front of a stone wall. The sweatshirt features watermelon graphics. They are also wearing a yellow headscarf.", "A black sweatshirt hangs against a textured pink wall. It features text reading \\"End the Occupation\\" in English and Arabic, with illustrations of watermelon slices integrated into the design.", "A woman with long brown hair stands outdoors near rocks and greenery. She is wearing a white T-shirt with images of watermelon slices and text. She has a serious expression and is looking at the camera.", "A white T-shirt hangs on a pink textured wall. The shirt displays the text \\"End the Occupation\\" in English and Arabic, along with images of watermelon slices.", "A person with curly hair stands against a pink wall, wearing a black t-shirt with the words \\"End the Occupation\\" and a tote bag on their shoulder. Their expression is serious.", "A black T-shirt hanging against a textured pink wall. The shirt features a graphic with text in bold white and Arabic, reading \\"END THE OCCUPATION\\" with a sliced watermelon design integrated into the text.", "A person with curly hair stands against a weathered blue wall. They wear a black long-sleeve shirt with bold white text that reads \\"END THE OCCUPATION.\\" The setting is simple with a focus on the message.", "A black long-sleeve shirt hanging on a hanger against a textured pink wall. The shirt has text that reads \\"END THE OCCUPATION\\" in English and Arabic, alongside small graphics of watermelon slices.", "A person with long hair stands outdoors on a grassy path, wearing a white shirt with \\"End the Occupation\\" in black text and carrying a gray tote bag. They are surrounded by trees and rocks.", "A person with long hair stands on grass in front of a stone wall. They are wearing a white long-sleeve shirt with text and a graphic, blue jeans, and holding a gray bag. The setting appears rustic and outdoors.", "A white long-sleeve shirt hangs on a wire against a textured pink wall. The shirt features bold black text in English and Arabic that reads \\"End the Occupation,\\" with red and green watermelon slices integrated into the design.", "A person in a black shirt and light jeans holds a white tote bag with text in English and Arabic, displaying a watermelon design. They stand on grass with an ornate rug and a pink wall in the background.", "White tote bag against a pink wall with \\"End the occupation\\" written in English and Arabic, featuring a watermelon graphic.", "A person with curly hair stands outside, holding a black bag with text urging to end the occupation in English and Arabic. They wear a light purple shirt and dark pants, with a stone wall and greenery in the background.", "A black tote bag hanging on a textured pink wall. The bag features a design with the text \\"End the Occupation\\" in English and Arabic, along with watermelon illustrations.", "A person with a beard wearing a patterned scarf sits next to another person holding a green tote bag with the text \\"End the Occupation\\" in English and Arabic. The scene is outdoors with a patterned rug beneath them.", "A green tote bag with the phrase \\"End the Occupation\\" written in English and Arabic, along with a half watermelon illustration, hangs against a textured pink wall.", "A person is holding a tote bag with the phrase \\"End the Occupation\\" printed in English and Arabic, along with watermelon illustrations. They are standing against a red brick background, wearing a black top and blue jeans.", "A tote bag against a textured, pink wall. The bag features text in English and Arabic saying \\"End the Occupation\\" alongside images of watermelon slices.", "A woman with curly hair stands against a stone wall, wearing a light gray sweatshirt with floral designs and the text \\"from the flowers resist.\\" She has a netted bag and a long red and black floral skirt.", "Gray sweatshirt hanging on a hanger against a textured pink wall. The shirt features colorful floral designs and the phrase \\"Even the flowers resist\\" printed on the front.", "Size chart for a loose-fitting garment, showing size options from 4-6 to 5XL. Includes width and length in centimeters: smallest is 39 cm width, 52 cm length; largest is 78 cm width, 90 cm length.", "A woman with curly hair wears a black sweatshirt with floral designs and text, draped in a patterned shawl. She stands against a blue and white textured wall, looking directly at the camera.", "A person with curly hair stands in a garden, holding a plant. They're wearing a black sweatshirt with floral designs and text, along with a checkered scarf. Tall sunflowers and lush greenery fill the background under a cloudy sky.", "A black sweatshirt hangs on a wall with pinkish textures. It features embroidered flowers and the text \\"Even the flowers resist!\\" with additional small text below.", "Woman with curly hair smiles wearing a black hoodie with floral patterns and text reading \\"Even the flowers resist,\\" standing against a pink textured wall.", "A person wearing a dark hoodie and patterned pink skirt stands against a pink textured wall. They have the hood up and are glancing sideways, with one hand near their face. Grass grows along the base of the wall.", "Black hoodie on a hanger against a pink textured wall. It features a design of colorful flowers surrounding the text \\"Even the flowers resist.", "A person with curly hair smiles, wearing a black hoodie with the text \\"Even the flowers resist\\" and a floral pattern. The background is a pinkish wall.", "Size chart for a t-shirt showing measurements in centimeters. Sizes range from 1 to 8XL, detailing half-width and length for each size. Width starts at 30 cm for size 1 and ends at 78 cm for 8XL. Length starts at 36 cm and ends at 87 cm.", "A person in jeans and black sneakers sits on rocky steps, holding a white tote bag with floral designs and the text \\"Even the flowers resist.\\" They are wearing a black shirt with text and graphics. Shrubbery grows among the rocks.", "A woman stands outdoors on grass, wearing a white long-sleeve shirt with black text and a watermelon graphic, paired with blue jeans. She has a green tote bag over her shoulder. The background features stone walls and foliage.", "A white long-sleeved shirt on a hanger against a pink wall. The shirt has a graphic with watermelon slices and text saying \\"End the Occupation\\" in English and Arabic.", "A person wearing a white shirt with a graphic, a beige headscarf, and red lipstick stands in front of a patterned rug. The background features intricate designs and a red wall at the top. The individual is looking to the side.", "A woman wearing a blue graphic T-shirt and acid-wash jeans stands confidently with hands on hips. She has a headscarf and bold red lipstick. The background features a patterned rug in earth tones.", "Illustration of a classroom with overturned desks and chairs. A streamer hangs from the ceiling. Arabic text reads, \\"شعار أسبوع حقوق الطفل لعام 2024 هو حق الأطفال بالتعليم,\\" which means \\"Child Rights Week 2024 slogan: Children's right to education.", "A majestic mountain peak partially shrouded in clouds rises sharply against a cloudy sky. The rocky terrain at the base shows a mix of shadows and light, adding texture to the landscape.", "A towering, jagged mountain peak partly shrouded in clouds, set against a cloudy sky. The rugged terrain is a mix of rocky surfaces and sparse vegetation, highlighting the dramatic natural landscape.", "A majestic mountain peak shrouded in clouds rises above a rugged, rocky landscape. The dramatic view captures the steep slopes and edges of the formation under a cloudy sky, highlighting the natural grandeur of the scene.", "A repetitive pattern of black, curved leaf-like shapes aligned in a horizontal row against a white background. The design creates an optical illusion with its alternating direction and consistent spacing.", "Logo of Sumud, The Finnish Palestine Network. Features a stylized tree within a red semi-circle and text in Finnish, Arabic, and English.", "A majestic mountain peak shrouded in clouds under a blue sky. The rocky formation rises prominently above the rugged terrain, with slopes covered in loose stones and sparse vegetation.", "A majestic mountain peak surrounded by clouds against a clear blue sky. The rugged terrain features steep slopes with patches of snow and rocky outcrops. The scene conveys a serene and awe-inspiring natural beauty.", "A majestic mountain peak rises sharply, partially shrouded in clouds. The rocky terrain is a mix of light and dark grays with scattered vegetation. A dramatic sky with thick clouds enhances the striking landscape.", "A majestic mountain peak partially shrouded in clouds, with rugged, rocky slopes leading to its summit. The landscape is dramatic, with a mix of rocky terrain and patches of grass, under a cloudy sky.", "A majestic mountain peak surrounded by clouds, with rocky slopes and rugged terrain. The sky is slightly overcast, adding a dramatic effect to the scenic landscape.", "A serene mountain landscape with layers of mist-covered peaks. The distant silhouettes of the hills create a depth effect, blending into a soft, hazy sky. The overall tone is calming, with muted shades of blue and gray.", "A stunning mountain landscape featuring jagged peaks partially shrouded by clouds. The rocky terrain contrasts with the dramatic sky, creating a serene and awe-inspiring natural scene.", "A dramatic landscape featuring the Tre Cime di Lavaredo, three towering peaks arising from rocky terrain under a cloudy sky. The central peak is partially shrouded in mist, creating a mystical and majestic atmosphere.", "A majestic mountain peak, partly shrouded in clouds, rises from a rocky landscape under a cloudy sky. The rugged terrain and striking rock formations create a dramatic and awe-inspiring scene.", "A majestic, rocky mountain peak partially shrouded in clouds under a cloudy sky. The rugged terrain is barren with shades of gray and brown, highlighting the steep slopes and jagged ridges.", "A rugged mountain landscape featuring jagged peaks emerging from misty clouds. The grayish-brown rocky slopes are streaked with lighter patches, under a partly cloudy sky. The scene conveys a sense of isolation and natural grandeur.", "A majestic mountain peak covered partly in clouds, with jagged rock formations. The sky is overcast, creating a dramatic and moody atmosphere. The base has rocky slopes with sparse vegetation.", "A majestic mountain peak shrouded in clouds rises from a rugged, rocky slope. The sky is partly cloudy, casting soft shadows on the terrain, creating a dramatic and serene landscape scene.", "A person with a backpack and hiking poles walks through a sunlit forest, surrounded by tall trees and accompanied by a dog walking behind.", "Kuva: Nora Sayyad"]	[]	[]	[]
0ee906a9-faf9-4df8-ba81-96c86fececfb	0e525c36-d463-4caa-9e20-316dc966b8ba	en	Tampere: Sumud Tampere New Evening	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.240515	2026-01-05 11:55:51.240515	tampere-sumud-tampereen-uusien-ilta	published	Welcome to get to know Sumud Tampere's activities and members at the Newcomers' Evening Thursday 25 September, 18-20 . We meet in the Ritva room of Sampola Library (Sammonkatu 2).\n\nJoin us to write postcards to decision-makers or just enjoy good company. There will also be snacks on offer.\n\nAccessibility:\nTwo accessible parking spaces, ramp less than 6m from the parking space.\nThere is a door release button at the main door, some of the thresholds can be more than 2cm.\nAccessible toilet on the -1 floor.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-09-08 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-09-08 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Screenshot-2025-09-08-at-14-09-46-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
20020d0a-0a34-4d74-9299-6b1369045ec0	eb5a1132-3a0d-492a-be38-a43ca25a73db	en	Helsinki: Helsinki: Conversations on Cultural Boycotts	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.240934	2026-01-05 11:55:51.240934	helsinki-keskusteluja-kulttuurisesta-boikotista	published	BDS Finland will organise a Conversations on Cultural Boycott event on Friday, September 12, at 5-8 pm, at Parvisali on the 6th floor of Tekstin talo (Lintulahdenkatu 3, Helsinki).\n\nWe will gather up with artists and other professionals in cultural field in Mad House Helsinki to discuss the topic of cultural boycotts and explore how art and culture can play a powerful role in advancing the movement.\n\nAs previously announced, we are honored to have Omar Barghouti, co-founder of the Palestinian-led BDS movement, as our guest speaker. We will also hear about local campaings in the Finnish field of cultural boycotts such as Flow Strike, Finland Against Apartheid, EurovisiOFF and Apartheid Free Zone. After introductions there will be space for all of us to ask questions and engage in conversations around the topics.\n\nThe event is free of charge and there is no sign up.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-09-08 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-09-08 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Screenshot-2025-09-08-at-11-58-43-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
