178ceeeb-d063-4b84-9efb-3e36b33048fc	cd7d62cb-09ed-42de-8120-7f7fcda50a25	en	Kuopio: Demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.244978	2026-01-05 11:55:51.244978	kuopio-mielenosoitus-4	published	On Saturday 20 September at 1 PM we gather at Kuopio Market Square in front of the stage for a peaceful demonstration to show solidarity with the Palestinian people.\n\nThe event is organized by Health for Palestine, Kuopio for Palestine, BDS, Sumud Kuopio and Students for Palestine Kuopio. Representatives from these organizations will speak at the event. Crafts4gaza will be at the demo selling their products!\n\nThe UN has stated that Israel is causing famine in Gaza. We must act together, silence is not an option.\n\nJoin us with an open and low threshold, show your support and stand with us in demanding an end to genocide.\n\nThis is an apartheid free space. Welcome, every voice matters!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-09-19 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-09-19 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Screenshot-2025-09-19-at-08-44-49-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
2943b57b-8578-4006-8879-b22944b9e8e5	8a077479-7c83-4b87-9238-f106e9976db3	en	Hämeenlinna: Postcards to Politicians	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.245372	2026-01-05 11:55:51.245372	hameenlinna-postikortteja-paattajille	published	Welcome to write postcards to politicians to demand fair legislations for Palestine on Tuesday Sept 23rd at 4pm. The event is organised by Sumud Hämeenlinna and HAMK Students for Palestine.\n\nWe'll meet in front of Verkatehdas and walk close to an accessible space indoors. If you arrive after 4:10pm, send us a dm on Instagram (@hameenlinnawithpalestine or @hamkstudentsforpalestine) to get our exact location.\n\nWe'll bring postcards and we will provide stamps for the cards made in the workshop. If you want to contribute, you can also buy your own stamps or take empty postcards from home	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-09-19 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-09-19 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Screenshot-2025-09-19-at-09-05-56-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
e7fc1f97-3b61-4c4f-8573-562aeb6cad8d	\N	en	Helsinki: Antizionist Learning Circle	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.245767	2026-01-05 11:55:51.245767	helsinki-antizionist-learning-circle	published	Students for Palestine will organise an Antizionist Learning Circle on Tuesday 23.9. at 18.00-20.00 in TEAK, Haapaniemenkatu 6, Helsinki.\n\nIn this learning circle (part 10) we will collectively learn about the Second Intifada, or the Al-Aqsa Intifada, with Palestinian guest speakers.\n\nUpcoming learning circles on Palestinian Resistance:\n\nTUE 23.9. - SECOND INTIFADA\n\nTUE 21.10. - AL-AQSA FLOOD\n\nTUE 18.11. - INTERNATIONAL DAY OF SOLIDARITY WITH THE PALESTINIAN PEOPLE\n\nTUE 16.12. - FIRST INTIFADA\n\nWHAT? Facilitated co-learning session with learning materials varying from easy to approach to more time and dedication demanding.\n\nWHERE? TEAK (Teatterikorkeakoulu), Haapaniemenkatu 6, Helsinki (meet us in the lobby of TEAK at 17.45)\n\nWHEN? Tuesday 23.9. at 18.00-20.00\n\nWHO can attend? Everyone!\n\nHOW to participate? Ideally familiarize yourself in advance with one or more of the materials before Tuesday, but you are welcome to join also without prior knowlegde or reading<3 List of materials can be found from the linktr.ee in our Instagram bio @studentsforpalestinefinland.\n\nAccessibility: We’ll meet in the lobby of TEAK, and go together to the space. There is an elevator to the space.\n\nIt is possible to stop in front of the main door, and there is enough space for a taxi van, for example. The threshold-free main entrance to the building is 235 cm wide. Please note that the entrance door is not automated, and it may be heavy to open. If you need help with opening the door, you can find the info desk’s phone number on the door.\n\nThe Theatre Academy main building (Kookos) is accessible. Please note that the floor of the lobby is uneven, please be careful! Unfortunately, there is no induction loop available in the performance facilities. There are performance facilities on several different floors. All floors are accessible by a lift. There is an accessible toilet on the same floor as the main lobby (Tori). All toilets in the building are gender-neutral.\n\nMore info and a map on the website of Uniarts Helsinki (Theater Academy).	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-09-19 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-09-19 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Screenshot-2025-09-19-at-08-57-49-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
d952b570-4b39-4446-9ecd-3e1ca6769adb	8fe75a35-d0e4-43c4-a48f-f0589a6594f8	en	Kouvola: Palestine Cinema Days Screening	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.256811	2026-01-05 11:55:51.256811	kouvola-a-state-of-passion-elokuvanaytos	published	Sumud Kouvola screens Carol Mansour and Muna Khalid's documentary A State of Passion on Sunday 2.11. at 16:00 at Kulttuuritila Kuva-Portti in Kouvola.\n\nThe screening is part of Filmlab Palestine's annual Palestine Cinema Days event.\n\nThe screening is free of charge and you can book a place through this form.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-13 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-13 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-13-at-13-53-45-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
28c4c246-b4e5-45de-b23a-2f9ed2fbb49f	a32d24eb-47ef-4552-b98b-1efae21b67c9	en	Webinar: The Future of Palestine and the Future for Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.246178	2026-01-05 11:55:51.246178	webinaari-palestiinan-tulevaisuus-ja-tulevaisuus-palestiinalle	published	What is the future like for Palestine? What can we do for a future free Palestine? Welcome to discuss these questions at Sumud's webinar on Monday, October 6, from 5 pm to 7 pm. Participating in the discussion will be Bruno Jäntti, PhD researcher in Global Politics at the University of Helsinki, and Iiris Pajunen, Finnish-Palestinian activist and chair of Sumud Tampere.\n\nBruno Jäntti's introduction will discuss the future of Palestine from a geopolitical perspective. How likely are the different scenarios, for example of a two-state solution? What kind of roles and interests do different actors have? How can Finland influence the future of Palestine?\n\nIris Pajunen examines the question of the future of activism. Which forms of activism and organising are fruitful? What lessons have the last 2 years brought? How to maintain motivation for Palestine activism in the long term?\n\nThe language of the webinar is Finnish. Register for the webinar here.\n\nWelcome to join the discussion!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-09-19 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-09-19 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Webinaari-1.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
9313b252-fd2d-4ae8-8b9b-9100b921f077	5d60048a-afd4-4424-97aa-dadcc38b3632	en	Kouvola: Sumud Kouvola meeting	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.24661	2026-01-05 11:55:51.24661	kouvola-sumud-kouvolan-tapaaminen	published	Sumud Kouvola's next meeting will take place on Tuesday, October 7, at 5 pm at Galleria Loiva (Kouvolankatu 3). Newcomers are welcome again!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-09-19 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-09-19 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/signal-2025-09-21-164356_002-1.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
44eb1a0f-2911-4c42-9050-94625c988c45	\N	en	Zoom: Book Talks on Global Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.246995	2026-01-05 11:55:51.246995	helsinki-book-talks-on-global-palestine-2	published	The Finnish Institute in the Middle East (FIME) will organise a series of Book Talks on Global Palestine. The second talk will take place on Thursday, October 2, at 4:15-5:30 pm on Zoom.\n\nIn the second talk of the series, Rhys Machold discusses the police entanglements across India and Palestine/Israel and the efforts of Israel’s homeland security industry to advise and equip Indian city and state governments. Through a focus on the often unseen and overlooked political struggles at work in the making of homeland security, the book details how homeland security is a universalizing project, which seeks to remake the world in its image, and tells the story of how claims to global authority are fabricated and put to work.\n\nRegister here at the latest October 1.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-09-19 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-09-19 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Screenshot-2025-09-19-at-09-40-22-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
e0f2082e-cd0e-4c32-b7f3-3f9bd79459a9	6b424696-ec77-42f7-99da-79e155e55fca	en	Zoom: Book Talks on Global Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.247383	2026-01-05 11:55:51.247383	zoom-book-talks-on-global-palestine	published	The Finnish Institute in the Middle East (FIME) will organise a series of Book Talks on Global Palestine. The final talk will take place on Tuesday, October 14, at 4:15-5:30 pm on Zoom.\n\nIn the final part of the series, Muhannad Ayyash provides timely fresh perspective on Palestine-Israel by rethinking the nature of settler-colonial sovereignty and the relationship between land and people. Muhannad Ayyash argues that this relationship comes in two distinct forms: a settler-colonial type, practiced by the Israeli state, that consists of “lordship” over land and people, and a decolonial type, seen in Palestinian popular organizing, that he calls “land as life,” a reciprocal bond.\n\nRegister here at the latest October 13.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-09-19 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-09-19 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Screenshot-2025-09-19-at-09-40-22-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
