a7e673b6-a3ff-49f3-86e8-1f5094c252d0	e0fd1cb5-e65a-437c-a3d3-42c7425665ac	en	Helsinki: Human Chain Against the Genocide	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.252294	2026-01-05 11:55:51.252294	helsinki-ihmisketju-kansanmurhaa-vastaan-3	published	Palcif is organising a human chain against the genocide on Friday, October 3, at 5 pm at Kaivokatu, by City Center in Helsinki.\n\nJoin us to form the POTS & PANS human chain against the genocide and starvation of the Palestinian people.\n\nLet us show together that we will not accept violence, occupation, ethnic cleansing, starvation and apartheid!\n\nThere will be police present to monitor security.\nRacist, sexist or otherwise discriminatory symbols and slogans are not allowed.\nThere will be de-escalators at the event who you can turn to if you feel unsafe or have any concerns.\nWe will also have chanters who you can join in the chants - but you can also protest quietly if you feel more comfortable. Every way of being present is valuable.\nBring a pot, pan, spoon, plate, signs, friends and a voice for justice!\n\nThe demonstration is supported by Sumud, Sumud Helsinki, Finnish-Arab Friendship Society, Global movement to Gaza Finland, Äitikapina, Health for Palestine Finland and Crafts4Gaza.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-01 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-01 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-09-30-at-18.31.41.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
ddc577c0-3bdc-42cf-839c-b125049b9575	\N	en	Helsinki: Café Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.252691	2026-01-05 11:55:51.252691	helsinki-cafe-palestine-3-2	published	Sumud Helsinki and Palcif welcomes you to join the October Café Palestine on Sunday 5.10. in Kulttuurikeskus Oranssi.\n\nAddress: Kaasutehtaankatu 1, Suvilahti, Helsinki.\n\nThe café opens at 16.00 and the info session begins at 17.00. This time we’ll learn about protester’s rights at an hour-long session. This is a good opportunity to learn about our rights and hold on to them in coming protests. We see how protesters in Germany are being beaten by police and even deported. As long as we have our rights to protest we need to defend them and use them!\n\nFrom 18.00 free discussions and more sage tea!\n\nThe café closes at 19.00.\n\nWe offer coffee, tea and snacks. If you want, you are welcome to bring something to share. Bring your friends and family! Children are very welcome.\n\nAccessibility:\nThe Oranssi entrance, event facilities and toilet are at street level, and they can also accommodate larger aids. However, a few higher thresholds and sloping ramps may be a bit difficult for manual wheelchair users, for example. The toilets are gender-neutral.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-01 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-01 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-01-at-17-33-39-2-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
53cec048-74a3-4592-9683-dc14b5cf4b82	c6c458ee-74b5-401e-93b7-85f89227dcc5	en	Tampere: Free Palestine -Solidarity Night	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.253091	2026-01-05 11:55:51.253091	tampere-vapaa-palestiina-solidaarisuusilta	published	Free Palestine solidarity night on Thursday, October 16, at Kulttuuritalo Telakka, in Tampere. Doors open at 18.00.\n\nTickets from 15 € from Tiketti.\nYou can also buy a 25 € or 50 € support ticket.\n\nThe proceeds of the ticket sales will be donated to Doctors Without Borders. Between presentations there will be speeches on the situation in Palestine.\n\nPerformers include Kielo Kärkkäinen, Ville Leinonen, Juha Junttu, Hannibal Stark, Kiukkupussy, Reetta-Kaisa Iles, Jouko Enkelnotko and Liila Jokelin.\n\nHouse band: Arto Piispanen, Sami Sippola, Janne Tuomi, Ville Rauhala.\n\nIris Pajunen, the chair of Sumud Tampere will be speaking.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-01 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-01 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/telakka.jpg	\N	[]	[]	[]
00d23465-3998-484d-b299-a5c7aa506b0b	7dcbf781-6966-4136-af8a-1f7bf5aca496	en	Helsinki: No Association with Genocide -campaign event	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.253486	2026-01-05 11:55:51.253486	helsinki-ei-kumppanuutta-kansanmurhan-kanssa-kampanjatapahtuma	published	Students for Palestine & Researchers for Palestine are organizing a campaign event on Wednesday, the 15th of October in the University of Helsinki Main Building at 4-6 pm.\n\nCome learn about BDS, PACBI as well as academic boycott more broadly – and discover what our campaign is about in particular! Let’s join our forces as students, researchers and faculty to build the pressure needed for our institution to implement a full academic boycott of Israel! Together we can build the momentum and give courage to the University to take immediate principled action.\n\nThe event program consists of speeches, presentations and discussions. Come talk to us, learn more and sign a petition in support of academic boycott. There will be small snacks and coffee served in the event.\n\nWHAT? No Association with Genocide -campaign event\n\nWHEN? Wednesday 15.10. 16-18:00\n\nWHERE? Tekla Hultin (F3003), University of Helsinki Main building (Fabianinkatu 33)	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-06 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-06 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-06-at-13-47-02-1-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
698be759-27ae-48e0-8c7f-d7b64259039c	1f73ade0-ecf1-411a-a585-4961d15912c0	en	Turku: Reading Circle	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.253869	2026-01-05 11:55:51.253869	turku-lukupiiri-6	published	In October, Turku with Palestine will read "Resisting Erasure: Capital, Imperialism and Race in Palestine" by Adam Hanieh, Robert Knox and Rafeef Ziadah.\n\nWe will meet at Kirjakahvila on Thursday 23rd October 16:00-18:00 to discuss the book.\n\nThe 2025 pamphlet, published by Verso, emerged from a series of educational day schools organised by the group Workers in Palestine in the midst of the genocide in Gaza, and is an essential introduction for anyone looking to understand what Palestine reveals about the world.\n\nChallenging mainstream narratives that reduce Palestine to ancient hatreds, humanitarian tragedy, or legal abstractions, the book places Israeli settler-colonialism within the broader historical arc of imperialism, race, and fossil capitalism in the Middle East, and provides a thorough anti-imperialist critique of the forces that sustain the Israeli settler-colonial project today.\n\nThe discussion will in English and everyone is welcome! If you would like to have the ebook, you can email us at turkuwithpalestine@gmail.com\n\nIn the meeting we will also decide the next book to read together. All welcome!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-06 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-06 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-06-at-14-00-09-1-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
f3877e57-ef6a-4731-90dd-962220b5da18	7d49b8ec-b2e9-4f50-a1cc-551dd372731b	en	Kuopio: Students for Palestine Kuopio’s Newcomers’ evening	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.254258	2026-01-05 11:55:51.254258	kuopio-student-for-palestine-kuopion-uusien-ilta	published	Welcome to Students for Palestine Kuopio’s Newcomers’ evening on Monday, October 13, at 5-8 pm at Studentia chapel, Yliopistonranta 15, Kuopio!\n\nOur autum has had a lovely start with our initiative for the academic boycott gaining over 100 signatures and new actives joining our movement!\n\nWe know that there can be a high threshold for joining something new, though. Due to that, we want to lower that threshold with the help of our newcomers’ evening! You’ll be able to ask us whatever is on your mind while enjoying baked goods.\n\nSo — come hang out with us on Monday 13.10. from 17.00-20.00 in the Studentia chapel and learn more about us!\n\nWe’ll also be selling products by Crafts4Gaza, whose proceeds all go straight to Gaza.\n\nWHAT: Students for Palestine Kuopio’s Newcomers’ evening\nWHERE: Studentia chapel, Yliopistonranta 15, 70210 Kuopio\nWHEN: Mon 13.10, 17-20.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-06 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-06 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-06-at-14-12-45-1-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
