93cf8da8-fc26-4181-b871-8eb29ad37674	31d48bcd-9b14-417e-8dc3-122a49d84d58	en	Oulu: Palestine Book Club	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.255443	2026-01-05 11:55:51.255443	oulu-palestiina-kirjakerho	published	Sumud Oulu is organizing a Palestine Book Club!\n\nThe first meeting will be on the 26th of October in Café Palestine, at Kansankatu 53, Oulu (information regarding time coming later).\n\nWe’ll be discussing the first three chapters of: The Hundred Years’ War on Palestine: A History of Settler Colonialism and Resistance, 1917–2017 by Rashid Khalidi. While preferable to prepare by reading these chapters, you are welcome to join us even if you have not read everything before the meeting.\n\nThe book club will be held in either English or Finnish depending on the participants’ preferences.\n\nWe will offer coffee, tea and snacks. See you there!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-13 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-13 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-13-at-12-46-53-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
b09c4484-0c85-4967-ad7a-2876a20daf1f	4313dcf8-f4cf-4f05-80bb-946014f346a3	en	Helsinki: Refugee Film Festival	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.255845	2026-01-05 11:55:51.255845	helsinki-refugee-film-festival	published	The Refugee Film Festival, which focuses on refugee issues, is here again - welcome to Korjaamo Kino in Töölö, Helsinki, on 24-25 October 2025!\n\nOur new international films deal with Palestine, Afghanistan and Sudan. In the screening of New Domestic Films we will have short films by Ali Al-Saffu, Sherwan Haji, Zagros Manuchar and Tirdad Motavali.\n\nThe festival will open on Friday at 2 pm with a discussion led by the Support For Asylum Seekers on Finland’s international responsibility in the implementation of human rights and international law. The focus is particularly on Palestine.\n\nSaturday opens with world premier of Fokus-zoom, a 50 minute documentary by the team of Kerttu Matinpuro, Anni Mikkonen and association of Somali families from Lieksa. The team will come to RFF all the way from Northern Carelia. All welcome!\n\nThe poster of the seventh Refugee Film Festival is created by artist Mihigo Kenny.\n\nYou can find the program and ticket sales at Refugee Film Festival's website. See you at Korjaamo Kino!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-13 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-13 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-13-at-13-10-37-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
378c2122-c333-4459-b743-4f06a0c14bfb	cab2a206-9dc0-45ef-a87d-ba88700daa69	en	Vantaa: Demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.256219	2026-01-05 11:55:51.256219	vantaa-mielenosoitus	published	Palcif and Sumud Helsinki will organise a "From Vantaa to Palestine" demonstration against the genocide on Saturday 18.10. at 15-16:30. The march starts at the northern end of the Heureka parking lot (Kuninkaalantie 5, Vantaa) and ends at Tikkurilantori, next to the Vantaa City Hall.\n\nJoin the first demonstration organized by Palestinian communities in Vantaa to demand a an end to the genocide and starvation of Palestinians and a free Palestine. Together we will show that we do not accept violence, occupation, ethnic cleansing, starvation, apartheid or any other form of genocide!\n\nOnly Palestinian flags are allowed at the demonstration. Racist, sexist or otherwise discriminatory symbols and slogans that contain or incite hate speech are not allowed. There will be a police officer at the event to monitor security. There are de-escalators present who you can turn to if you feel unsafe or have any concerns. We also have shouters with whom you can participate in common slogans – but you can also demonstrate quietly if it feels more natural. Every way of being present is valuable! Bring signs, friends, and a voice for justice!\n\nAccessibility:\nThe route is relatively accessible, but there are two steeper ascents and descents at the beginning of the route. There are three road crossings on the route (there are pedestrian crossings, only one of which is a light intersection). At the Tikkurila health center, the bottleneck was a road construction site next to it on Kielotie, which is why the walking route will become narrower and continue narrow for a short distance on Asematie.\n\nSupporters: Finnish-Arab Friendship Society, Health for Palestine Finland, Mothers' Rebellion Finland, Crafts4Gaza and Students for Palestine Finland.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-13 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-13 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-13-at-13-43-32-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
b6b6d9e9-6a3f-44f9-8ce1-b42c0603259d	2e89800d-60a5-4201-bf65-70d78695d015	en	Helsinki: Gaza: Doctors Under Attack Documentary Screening	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.257592	2026-01-05 11:55:51.257592	helsinki-gaza-doctors-under-attack-dokumenttinaytos	published	Welcome to watch Karim Shah's documentary Gaza: Doctors Under Attack, which takes you inside Gaza hospitals to hear accounts from doctors there.\n\nAs part of the genocide, Israel is systematically destroying Gaza's healthcare system.\n\nDiscussion after the documentary.\n\nTime: Thursday 16.10.2025 at 17.30\nVenue: Oranssi, Kaasutehtaankatu 1, Helsinki\n\nOrganisers:\nFinnish-Arab Friendship Society AKYS\nPalestinian Community in Finland PALCIF\nHealth for Palestine Finland	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-13 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-13 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-13-at-14-22-18-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
65d96da4-233b-489c-a069-9e060c1c1f54	27f5133f-54f5-4dc7-986d-815cdd70c96f	en	Espoo: Gaza Calling Espoo	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.257998	2026-01-05 11:55:51.257998	espoo-gaza-calling-espoo	published	Espoo Theatre's Gaza Calling Espoo event on Saturday 15 November, at 16-20 at Espoo Theatre, &Revontuli, Revontulentie 8A.\n\nThrough readings, video messages, talks, and live music, Gaza calling Espoo brings the human face of Gaza closer to Finland. The event is part of breaking the silence around the genocide. We will also make a direct telephone connection to Gaza.\n\nPerformances and speeches will be in Finnish, English, and Arabic. Partially subtitled. You can see the entire program at the Espoo Theatre's web page.\n\nProceeds from the event will be donated to Gaza through Doctors Without Borders.\n\nTickets are on sale here.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-13 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-13 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-13-at-14-32-14-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
d9a4922a-0178-4367-87c2-aff2f48b9cbd	6adc841a-959a-4b02-922f-7fdb0d9c8dc5	en	Hämeenlinna: Palestine Cinema Days Screening	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.258373	2026-01-05 11:55:51.258373	hameenlinna-the-dupes-elokuvanaytos	published	Sumud Hämeenlinna and Hamk Students for Palestine organise a free film screening Beer restaurant Birger (Raatihuoneenkatu 5, Hämeenlinna) on Sunday 2.11. at 17.00 .\n\nThe Dupes (1973, dir. Tewfik Saleh) tells the story of three Palestinian men who seek a better life in Kuwait. They decide to trust a retired soldier and current smuggler who promises to take them to their destination. Can the smuggler be trusted and will the men make it under the burning sun?\n\nThe film is based on the novel Men in the sun by Ghassan Kanafan. Kanafani focused his stories on giving voice to the Palestinian struggle for independence and liberation from occupation. Kanafani is an award-winning Palestinian writer and journalist who was assassinated by Mossad with a car bomb in 1972.\n\nThe film will be followed by an optional discussion on how the drama of 1973 relates to today's world, and to the ongoing struggle for Palestinian liberation from occupation.\n\nThe film is in Arabic with subtitles in English.\n\nSumud - The Finnish Palestine Network will screen films from the Palestine Cinema Days Around the World 2025 film festival in several cities on the day of the Balfour Declaration on 2 November, the crucial day for the declaration of the State of Israel on Palestinian land 108 years ago. The presenting cities in Finland are Helsinki, Hämeenlinna, Tampere, Kouvola and Jyväskylä.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-15 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-15 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-15-at-13-29-44-1-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
640b08eb-ae21-4e2a-b24e-2aebb5a379e4	ac124f11-a4c7-467e-9523-ff816ff6ac4d	en	Jyväskylä: Fundraiser	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.258776	2026-01-05 11:55:51.258776	jyvaskyla-myyjaiset	published	Free Palestine JKL organises a fundraising sale on Monday, October 27, at 4-8 pm at Vakiopaine, Jyväskylä.\n\nGaza's borders have opened due to the latest ceasefire, and although Israel already breaks it constantly, this a critical moment to collect resources to aid the surviving population. The cost of life in Gaza has skyrocketed in the past months, and most people can't afford basic necessities, such as food and water. Due to the relentless israeli bombing of Gaza, most people are also homeless and need resources to rebuild their lives.\n\nWe warmly welcome you to our fundraiser to donate to Gaza for second-hand products of all kinds!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-21 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-21 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-21-at-09-10-58-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
35bd0207-284a-4581-9965-4908ba9d8860	8ca39499-860a-4491-b1ea-2ca7b3ef35c8	en	Tampere: bicycle marathon	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.259172	2026-01-05 11:55:51.259172	tampere-polkupyoramarssi	published	Peace Defenders, Sumud Tampere and Tampere with Palestine organise a bicycle march for Palestine Saturday 25 October at 15:00 Tampere.\n\nA ceasefire does not yet mean a just peace, and the oppression and suffering of the Palestinians is not over.\n\nThe march will start at 15:00 from Aleksanteri Church, and will continue along the route Hämeenkatu - Pikku kakkosen Park - Rongankatu - Vellamonkatu - Tammela Stadium - Itsenäisyydenkatu - Rongankatu - Laikku - Hämeenkatu - Aleksanteri Church.\n\nWelcome to join us!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-21 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-21 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-21-at-09-13-10-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
35fa887f-5915-466b-8a55-9dbb1bc9d3e5	efa20fdf-7b35-45f9-b57c-76c781f565f9	en	Helsinki: Protest at the University of Helsinki	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.259562	2026-01-05 11:55:51.259562	helsinki-mielenosoitus-helsingin-yliopistolla	published	Researchers for Palestine will organise a protest on Wednesday, October 29, at 3-5 pm in Porthania lobby, University of Helsinki.\n\nDear University of Helsinki employee, are you tired of decision-making that keeps ignoring the university's values and our voices as members of the university community?\n\nThe board and faculty council elections are coming up; it's time to change the direction. Let's join our forces for a more just, accountable, transparent and inclusive university!\n\nCome to Porthania Lobby on Wednesday, October 29, from 15-17 to demand better university democracy and find out how you can ask your candidate to commit to more open, inclusive and ethical decision-making in your workplace.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-21 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-21 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-21-at-09-56-43-1-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
016eb82b-e407-41be-b6cb-ec369c584b41	\N	en	Helsinki: Café Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.260111	2026-01-05 11:55:51.260111	helsinki-cafe-palestine-4-2	published	Welcome to Café Palestine organised by Sumud Helsinki on Sunday, November 2.\n\nAddress: Kulttuurikeskus Oranssi, Kaasutehtaankatu 1, Suvilahti.\n\nThis time we will take part in the Palestine Cinema Days and screen two short films.\n\nThe café opens at 16.00 with snacks, tea and coffee. The screenings start at 16:30. First we will see the short film Upshot (34 min) and next Jenin Jenin (54 min). From 18:15 free discussions on the films, upcoming events or anything else, plus more sage tea. The café closes at 19.00.\n\nIf you want, you are welcome to bring something to the table to share. Bring your friends and family!\n\nChildren are very welcome, but the films contain violence.\n\nAccessibility:\nThe Oranssi entrance, event facilities and toilet are at street level, and they can also accommodate larger aids. However, a few higher thresholds and sloping ramps may be a bit difficult for manual wheelchair users, for example. The toilets are gender-neutral.\n\nWe can't promise that the space is totally quiet during the screenings.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-21 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-21 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-21-at-10-02-49-1-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
d3b108f2-097f-4108-ad78-a77217c236d3	5af9a9ac-1cfd-42ac-8e61-77665bbe57a8	en	Helsinki: Palestine Cinema Days Screening	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.260497	2026-01-05 11:55:51.260497	helsinki-when-i-saw-you-elokuvanaytos	published	Queer Roihis screens the film When I Saw You on Sunday, November 2, at 4 pm at Roihuvuoren kylätalo. The screening is part of the global Palestine Cinema Days event.\n\nJordan, 1967. Having been separated from his father in the chaos of war, Tarek, 11, and his mother Ghaydaa, are amongst this latest wave of refugees. Placed in "temporary" refugee camps made up of tents and prefab houses until they would be able to return, they wait, like the generation before them who arrived in 1948. With difficulties adjusting to life in Harir camp and a longing to be reunited with his father, Tarek searches a way out, and discovers a new hope emerging with the times. Eventually his free spirit and curious nature lead him to a group of people on a journey that will change their lives.\n\nThe event is free and open for everyone. The accessibility information will be published soon on the Instagram account @queerroihis. Welcome!\n\nName of the film: When I Saw You\nDirectror: Annemarie Jacir\nProduction countries: Palestine, Jordan\nYear: 2012\nDuration: 93 min\nLanguage: The film is spoken in Arabic and subtitled in English	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-21 03:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-21 03:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-21-at-10-24-11-1-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
