41cb52e2-6722-4319-a651-28c584cbcfc8	\N	en	Helsinki: Silent Candlelight March	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.261264	2026-01-05 11:55:51.261264	helsinki-silent-candlelight-march	published	Place: Rautatientori, Helsinki\nTime: Perjantaina 31.10.2025 klo 17:00\n\nJoin the silent candlelight march organised by Palcif to respect over 70 000 Palestinian victims, of whom more than 20 000 are children. The march is silent and peaceful. Bring a candle and friends and family with you. Let's show together that we do not accept violence, occupation, ethnic cleansing or apartheid. The police will be at the event to monitor security. Racist, sexist or otherwise discriminating symbols and slogans are not allowed. There are de-escalators present who you can turn to if you feel unsafe or have any concerns.\n\nThe supporters of the event are Sumud Helsinki, Finnish-Arab Friendship Society, Global Movement 2 Gaza Finland, Mothers’ Rebellion Finland, Health for Palestine Finland ja Crafts4Gaza.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-27 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-27 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/WhatsApp-Image-2025-10-24-at-14.31.13.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
d2a7372b-8dac-46fa-8e61-8383c45a48d8	\N	en	Vantaa: Demonstration for Palestine	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.261633	2026-01-05 11:55:51.261633	vantaa-demonstration-for-palestine	published	Health for Palestine Finland will organise a demonstration for Palestine on Tuesday, 28.10.2025, at 16:30–17:30, at Peijas Hospital (Sairaalakatu 1, Vantaa).\n\nHealthcare work attire is welcome for protesters. Please feel free to bring your own sign. The protest is silent – we will not chant slogans or make noise that could disturb patient care. Racist, sexist, or otherwise discriminatory symbols or behavior are not allowed. You may bring a Palestinian flag. To keep the focus on Palestine, please do not bring other flags.\n\nThe demonstration is co-organised with Palcif. Sumud Helsinki and Global Movement 2 Gaza Finland support the demonstration.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-27 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-27 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-27-at-16-18-11-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
9d97b629-6535-44c7-992e-f58ff9d47e84	\N	en	Helsinki: Palestine Cinema Days Screening	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.262008	2026-01-05 11:55:51.262008	helsinki-film-screening	published	Kiila and Sumud Helsinki in collaboration with Cinema Orion will organise a Palestine Cinema Days film screening on Sunday, November 2, from 13:00-16:00, at Cinema Orion, Eerikinkatu 15, Helsinki.\n\nFilms:\nMaha Haj: Upshot (34 min)\nAnnemarie Jacir: When I Saw You (98 min)\n\nThe screening is free of charge.\n\nWelcome all!\n\nCollaborators: Filmlab Palestine, Cinema Orion, Sumud Helsinki	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-28 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-28 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-28-at-11-01-48-1-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
37b6173c-eb0d-49ba-86a6-2e9575f3f45a	\N	en	Tampere: Palestine Cinema Days Screening	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.262383	2026-01-05 11:55:51.262383	tampere-film-screening	published	Arthouse Cinema Niagara and Sumud Tampere will organise a Palestine Cinema Days Around the World film screening on Sunday, November 2, at 11.00 at Arthouse Cinema Niagara in Tampere.\n\nFilms:\nMaha Haj: UPSHOT (2024) 34 min\nMohammad Bakri: JENIN, JENIN (2003) 54 min\n\nThe movies will have subtitles in English. Age limit: 18. The screening is free of charge and organised together with Sumud Tampere.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-28 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-28 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-28-at-11-15-00-1-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
ba1894fe-57a0-4e6e-9a2a-1538701ff35b	\N	en	Espoo: Palestine Cinema Days Screening	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.26279	2026-01-05 11:55:51.26279	espoo-film-screening	published	Palestine Cinema Days Screening at Cinema Sheryl\n\nSaturday, November 1\n18:00-21:00\nCinema Sheryl, Aalto University, Espoo\n\nFree entry (no tickets needed)\n\nJoin Critical Cinema Lab and Cinema Sheryl, in collaboration with Aalto Students for Palestine, for a special screening as part of Palestine Cinema Days Around the World 2025: a global festival organized by Filmlab Palestine. Over 500 screenings take place around the world. This global effort is a show of solidarity with Palestine, an act of amplification for censored Palestinian voices, and a contribution to shifting the distorted narrative.\n\nAfter the film, there will be a discussion on the themes of complicity, silence, and responsibility within academic institutions and society in Finland.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-28 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-28 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-28-at-11-34-20-1-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
c0832aa1-4d8a-4ad3-b7f9-2d1e1ee0060e	\N	en	Turku: Palestine Cinema Days Screening	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.263181	2026-01-05 11:55:51.263181	turku-palestine-cinema-days-screening	published	Palestine Cinema Days in Turku\n\nOn the somber anniversary of the Balfour Declaration, November 2nd, Turku with Palestine will screen two films at 14:30 at Kirjakahvila, Turku: a documentary "Jenin, Jenin" (2002, dir. Mohammed Bakri) and a fiction film "When I Saw You" (2012, dir. Annemarie Jacir). Free entry!\n\n"JENIN, JENIN" (2002)\nThe film is set in March 2002 and tells of Israeli troops marching into the Palestinian refugee camp of Jenin, razing much of the camp to the ground and killing scores of civilians. Israel is accused of committing war crimes, prompting the United Nations to assign an independent commission to visit the camp which was subsequently denied entry by Israel.\n\nFilmmaker Mohammed Bakri visits the demolished camp and interviews survivors of all ages. Men, women, children address the harrowing days they have gone through, the anger and fear that they have experienced, but also the sentiment of being completely left alone by the Arab and the international community.\n\n"WHEN I SAW YOU" (2012)\n\n1967. The world is alive with change: brimming with reawakened energy, new styles, music and an infectious sense of hope. In Jordan, a different kind of change is underway as tens of thousands of refugees pour across the border from Palestine. Having been separated from his father in the chaos of war, Tarek, 11, and his mother Ghaydaa, are amongst this latest wave of refugees. Placed in "temporary" refugee camps made up of tents and prefab houses until they would be able to return, they wait, like the generation before them who arrived in 1948.\n\nWith difficulties adjusting to life in Harir camp and a longing to be reunited with his father, Tarek searches a way out, and discovers a new hope emerging with the times. Eventually his free spirit and curious nature lead him to a group of people on a journey that will change their lives. When I Saw You is the story of people affected by the times around them, in search of something more in their lives. A journey full of adventure, love, humor, and the desire to be free.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-28 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-28 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-28-at-11-56-05-1-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
a2cad6bf-60b7-47ec-9140-29be8036f23b	\N	en	Rovaniemi: Protest March	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.263571	2026-01-05 11:55:51.263571	rovaniemi-protest-march	published	Roimielenosoitus will organise a protest for Palestine on Saturday 8.11. at 3pm. We’ll gather for a march in Rovaniemi’s City Library (Jorma Eton tie 6).\n\nWe demand for the city of Rovaniemi to cut all ties with the state of Israel because it is committing a genocide in Gaza.\n\nAbout the program: we’ll march from the City Library to Sampoaukio. In Sampoaukio we will have a die-in, which means everyone will lay on the ground pretending to be dead. After that we’ll hear speeches, and the demo will end.\n\nItems to take with you: signs, flags, warm clothes, earplugs, pots and pans to make some noise.\n\nSee you in November!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-28 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-28 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-28-at-12-16-18-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
ed4a7f08-4a25-47b9-9abb-b7c02f7ced10	6e2345e5-a33f-4c9b-bb5c-a03bc2d90c6a	en	Helsinki: Club Solidarity	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.26394	2026-01-05 11:55:51.26394	helsinki-club-solidarity	published	Club Solidarity - live performances and club music – free entrance!\n\nWe welcome you to Club Solidarity!\n\nStudents for Palestine are throwing a party on the 7th of November at Mad House (Tekstin Talo, Parvisali, floor 6, Lintulahdenkatu 3, 00530 Helsinki). Doors will open at 19.00 and the event ends at 01.00.\n\nCome chill, dance and strengthen bonds with the community – as well as enjoy performances by local artists and activists. Club Solidarity is a night for each and everyone of us struggling for a free Palestine.\n\nThere will be many local artists and dj’s performing from easy and soft vibes to joyful and upbeat rhythms! The program also includes speeches and collaborations with organisers who are in solidarity with Palestine.\n\nWe will also raise funds for Gaza, through pay-what-you-can tickets and crafts by Crafts4gaza.\n\nACCESSIBILITY INFO: Find the accessibility information of at the webpage of Tekstin talo.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-10-28 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-10-28 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Screenshot-2025-10-28-at-12-24-04-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
0995993a-4745-4da1-bed7-e532222ba6d8	\N	en	Tampere: Protest	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.264314	2026-01-05 11:55:51.264314	tampere-protest	published	Tampere with Palestine will organise an End the Occupation protest on Saturday, November 8, at 5 pm at Hämeensilta in Tampere.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-11-05 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-11-05 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-05-at-10-20-44-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
4dd00837-4056-4d69-b32d-5a3601977940	\N	en	Helsinki: Demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.264679	2026-01-05 11:55:51.264679	helsinki-demonstration-3	published	Health for Palestine Finland will organise a demonstration on Wednesday, November 19, at 16.30-18 at the New Children’s Hospital (Stenbäckinkatu 9, Building 6, 00290 Helsinki).\n\nWhen children’s rights are crushed, there is nothing to celebrate.\nThis year, Children’s Rights Day is not a celebration, but a reminder that there are children in the world who can no longer be children.\n\nPalestinian children live amid constant terror.\nThey see more than any child should ever have to see.\nThey are children who have lost their parents,\nchildren who have had their arms and legs amputated without anesthesia because there are no medicines.\nChildren who wake and sleep to the sound of drones, for whom the sky no longer represents freedom but fear.\nChildren who have been stripped of childhood, safety, and joy.\n\nWhat we have just described is not only a tragedy—it is the reason why evacuation is necessary.\n\n15,600 Palestinian patients—13,800 of them children—urgently need evacuation from Gaza, as there is no longer a functioning hospital system or adequate emergency care.\n740 patients, including 137 children, have died while waiting for permission to leave for treatment.\n\nThis year, the theme of Children’s Rights Week in finland is #Saankuulua #saatkuulua.\nBut are the voices of Palestinian children being heard?\nCan you hear their cries for help, their tears, and their fears that the world can no longer ignore?\n\nWe demand that Finland acts now.\nThat Finland evacuates wounded and critically ill children for treatment.\nWe have the expertise. We have the resources. And above all, we have a moral obligation.\n\nPalestinian children are children, just like any others.\nThey have the right to life, education, health, safety, and a future.\n\nJoin us\nWednesday, 19 November 2025, 16:30–18:00\nNew Children’s Hospital, Stenbäckinkatu 9, Building 6, 00290 Helsinki\n\nHealthcare workwear is welcome for demonstrators. Feel free to bring your own sign. This demonstration is silent—we do not shout slogans or create noise that could disturb patient care.\n\nRacist, sexist, or otherwise discriminatory symbols or behavior are not allowed. To keep the focus on Palestine, please bring only Palestinian flags.\n\nThis demonstration is supported by Palcif, Sumud Helsinki, Äitikapina.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-11-05 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-11-05 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-05-at-10-47-10-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
