d617bb7b-ab4c-4bd1-89a2-745ffe20c81d	\N	en	Turku: Children’s Gaza – A Stage for Life and Death	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.266376	2026-01-05 11:55:51.266376	turku-childrens-gaza-a-stage-for-life-and-death	published	Children’s Gaza – a stage for life and death is a multidisciplinary art event based on real life stories of children from Gaza that takes place at Barker Theatre in Turku on 15th of November 2025 at 4 pm.\n\nAfter a break the event will continue as a candle march by the river at 6 pm. You can choose your entrance fee between 10 to 200 €. All the proceeds of the event will be donated to Doctors Without Borders.\n\nOrganizers of the event: Aura Company, Aura of Puppets, Barker Theatre, Grus Grus Theatre, Tehdas Theatre, Turku With Palestine, Activists for Palestine, Suomen arabialainen neuvosto.\n\nPhoto: Justus Anttila/ Eve Mäkitalo	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-11-10 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-11-10 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Ihmettelimme-raunioiden-merta.-Tuntui-silta-kuin-emme-olisi-koskaan-elaneet-ja-varttuneet-taalla.-Isani-osoitti-sormellaan-ja-sanoi-kahealla-aanella-Tassa…-tassa-oli-kotimme.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
0f748aca-65c0-466d-b1f5-df94736efa06	\N	en	Turku: Children’s Gaza – March of Fire and Light for the Palestinian Children	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.26676	2026-01-05 11:55:51.26676	turku-childrens-gaza-march-of-fire-and-light-for-the-palestinian-children	published	Children’s Gaza – March of fire and light for the Palestinian children on Saturday, 15th of November, at 6 pm in Turku.\n\nGathering by the river at the corner of Ursininkatu and Läntinen Rantakatu, Turku.\n\nTurku-based artists and communities invite everyone to join a silent procession for the lives of Palestinian children and in memory of those lost. Bring candles, Palestinian flags, or signs of solidarity.\n\nPicture: Eve Mäkitalo	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-11-10 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-11-10 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Kulkue3.jpg	\N	[]	[]	[]
98d9b432-1056-4498-b189-890f1e4e5d7b	\N	en	Helsinki: Joint Action	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.267128	2026-01-05 11:55:51.267128	helsinki-joint-action	published	JOINT ACTION: Together Against Genocide - Peace For Sudan and Palestine on Saturday, November 15, at 3 pm, at the Railway Square in Helsinki.\n\nThe action is organised by Civil Solidarity Movement for Palestine and Sudan and it is supported by Palcif, Sudanese Community in Finland, Sumud Helsinki, Global Movement for Gaza, Arab-Finnish Friendship Society, Health for Palestine Finland, Crafts4Gaza and Students for Palestine.\n\nFrom Sudan to Palestine, millions have been resisting genocide for over two years. In Sudan, despite the heroic efforts of local communal kitchens, over 20 millions are facing acute food insecurity. In Palestine, over 2 millions in Gaza endure bombardment, forced starvation and siege with steadfast Sumud, while violent repression escalates in the West Bank.\n\nWhile the ceasefire has been violated over 50 times in Gaza, the genocide continues with impunity in Darfur, Sudan. It is time for us to stand together to demand peace and liberation for Sudan and Palestine from all forms of Western imperialism enabling these atrocities.\n\nWe won’t be free until all of us are free!\n\nJoin us to raise our voices and demand an end to the genocide!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-11-10 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-11-10 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/WhatsApp-Image-2025-11-10-at-13.45.36.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
74dfcafc-ae53-4510-a737-f9d45c2288f9	\N	en	Tampere: Don't be alone	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.267512	2026-01-05 11:55:51.267512	tampere-dont-be-alone	published	Sumud Tampere and Lähi-idän naisten yhdistys ry will organise a Don't be alone event on Sunday 30.11., on the International Day of Solidarity, to cook Syrian-Palestinian food together, dance Dabke, and remember martyrs we have lost. Participants are encouraged to bring photos and stories of martyrs and family members that have been lost in war.\n\nWe'll meet in the youth centre Kolo on the 0 floor of Koskikeskus in Tampere.  Doors will open at 14:00 and close already at 14:05.\n\nSpace is available for 100 participants. Sign up: https://forms.gle/LLL7jiLZiX5mxgEj8\n\nThis event is in collaboration with Lähi-idän naisten yhdistys. They offer activities such as Dabke-classes every Sunday.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-11-14 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-11-14 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/photo_2025-11-12_13-26-05.jpg	\N	[]	[]	[]
c5f26c44-bf3b-4051-ae52-369befae3231	\N	en	Tampere with Palestine: Newcomers' Night	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.267868	2026-01-05 11:55:51.267868	tampere-with-palestine-newcomers-night	published	Tampere with Palestine will organise a newcomers' night on Saturday 22.11. at 17:00!\n\nTampere with Palestine is looking for individuals interested in and ready to work in the collective to organize different types of events that support and help the Palestine cause. At this gathering they will be introducing the collective, the work they do and how they do it. In addition, there will be some workshops, a Crafts4gaza table and general socializing.\n\nDM @tamperewithpalestine in Instagram if you'd like to join the event on 22.11. and they will provide you with the location details.\n\nWelcome!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-11-17 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-11-17 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-17-at-10-18-52-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
ff37b5c0-bb24-42db-a81a-d26f51a0706e	\N	en	Helsinki: Afganistan and Palestine Cultural Day for Children and Youth	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.268224	2026-01-05 11:55:51.268224	helsinki-afganistan-and-palestine-cultural-day-for-children-and-youth	published	Kampa collective in cooperation with Silti Minä Nousen ry and Vuosaari library will organise an Afganistan and Palestine Cultural Day for Children and Youth on Saturday, November 22, at 11:30-15 at Vuosaari library.\n\nThe event is organised as part of Children's Rights Week.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-11-17 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-11-17 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-17-at-12-53-15-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
9242fc6c-1378-4926-99dd-fc6d866df6b3	\N	en	Helsinki: International Day of Solidarity with the Palestinian People	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.268581	2026-01-05 11:55:51.268581	helsinki-international-day-of-solidarity-with-the-palestinian-people	published	The Palestinian Community In Finland (PALCIF) and the Finnish-Arab Friendship Society (AKYS) will organise a solidarity day event on the UN International Palestine Solidarity Day on Saturday, 29.11.2025, at 3:00 PM - 6:00 PM. The event will take place at Arbis, Dagmarinkatu 3, Helsinki. The ballroom is on the 2nd floor, accessible.\n\nThe event will feature Arabic and Finnish musical performances, Palestinian DABKEH dance, short documentaries and speeches.\n\nThe program includes a speech by former Foreign Minister Erkki Tuomioja, performances by Finnish singer Paleface, Palestinian singer Hakam, Syrian singer Fardoos Helal and DJ Abdo, AL-Huriya Dabke group, as well as speeches by representatives of numerous political parties and associations.\n\nPalestinian pastries, coffee and Palestinian Salvia tea will be served. Crafts4Gaza merch table will be in the place.\n\nYou are most welcome!	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-11-24 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-11-24 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/WhatsApp-Image-2025-11-22-at-21.31.48.jpeg	\N	[]	[]	[]
7bf64d85-aee6-4e2e-96e1-49bfb89c5629	\N	en	Helsinki: Light a Candle Demonstration	\N	\N	2026-01-05 11:55:51.268934	2026-01-05 11:55:51.268934	helsinki-light-a-candle-demonstration	published	Healthcare workers in Finland are joining Amnesty activists in lighting candles to honor Palestinian healthcare professionals unjustly detained in Israeli prisons. Together, they call for the immediate release of Dr. Abu Safiya and all 105 Palestinian healthcare workers who remain unlawfully imprisoned under harsh and degrading conditions.\n\nOn 27 December 2024, Israeli forces stormed Kamal Adwan Hospital - the last functioning hospital in North Gaza at the time - and arrested the hospital’s director Dr. Hussam Abu Safiya along with other medical staff and patients.\n\nThe arrest and arbitrary detention of health workers from Gaza is part of Israel’s systematic decimation of the healthcare system in Gaza. The intentional creation of conditions calculated to destroy Palestinians in Gaza constitutes an act of genocide.\n\nWe are gathering on Friday, November 28, at 17-18, at Narinkkatori where we will light candles for detained doctors and nurses. We will provide candles, but you can bring your own if you wish.\n\nWe will also provide ready-made signs. Please do not bring flags. Racist, sexist, or discriminatory texts and symbols are not allowed.\n\nThe demonstration is organised by Amnesty's Finnish section, Sumud, Health for Palestine Finland and the Palestinian Community in Finland.	\N	sumud.office	sumud.office	2025-11-24 02:00:00	\N	\N	2025-11-24 02:00:00	https://www.sumud.fi/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-11-24-at-10-39-24-Instagram.png	\N	[]	[]	[]
